Ecotopia Emerging ( EE ) by Ernest Callenbach is a fictionalized history of the events leading up to the secession of Northern California , Oregon , and Washington to form the steady - state , environmentalist nation of Ecotopia along the Pacific Coast of the United States .
The Sound Pattern of English ( frequently referred to as SPE ) is a 1968 work on phonology ( a branch of linguistics ) by Noam Chomsky and Morris Halle .
My Cousin Rachel is a novel by British author Daphne du Maurier , published in 1951 .
Azemia is a satirical novel , written by William Thomas Beckford , that was first published in 1797 .
Reversible Errors , published in 2002 ( paperback edition by Picador , 2003 ) is Scott Turow 's sixth novel , and like the others , set in fictional Kindle County .
`` Elle me contrôle '' is a song by French singer M. Pokora written and composed by Georges Padey , Kore & Skalp , Matt Pokora , Da Team and Sweety .
The Diary of a Nobody is an English comic novel written by the brothers George and Weedon Grossmith , with illustrations by the latter .
The Order of Vladimir , Third Class ( Russian : Владимир третьей степени ; Vladimir tret'jej stepeni ) is an unfinished play by Nikolai Gogol , which he worked on between 1832 and 1834 .
The Secret of the League is a 1907 dystopian novel by Ernest Bramah , which describes the overthrow of a democratically - elected British Labour Party Government through a carefully prepared plot by members of the upper classes , and depicts such an overthrow as being a positive and desirable outcome .
A Man Without a Country ( subtitle : A Memoir Of Life In George W Bush 's America ) is an essay collection published in 2005 by the author Kurt Vonnegut .
Tomb of Horrors is an adventure module written by Gary Gygax for the Dungeons & Dragons ( D&D ) role - playing game .
Phaladeepika is a treatise on Hindu astrology written by Mantreswara .
Going Bovine is a 2009 surreal dark comedy novel by Libba Bray .
The Satin Slipper ( Le Soulier de satin ) is a long play by the French dramatist and poet Paul Claudel .
Aún soltera is the first book of the Uruguayan Dani Umpi .
Fontamara ( fontaˈmaːra ) is a 1933 novel by the Italian author Ignazio Silone , written when he was a refugee from the Fascist Police in Davos , Switzerland .
Old Soldiers ( 2005 ) is a sequel novel to the short story `` With Your Shield '' by David Weber , published in the anthology Bolo ! , edited by the same writer .
The Last Boer War is a 1899 non - fiction book by H. Rider Haggard about the Boer War of 1881 .
Journey to the Alcarria ( Spanish : Viaje a la Alcarria ) is a travel book by the Spanish Nobel Prize - winning author Camilo José Cela .
Empire of a Thousand Planets is volume two in the French comic book ( or bande dessinée ) science fiction series Valérian and Laureline created by writer Pierre Christin and artist Jean - Claude Mézières .
Sundown Beach is a 1948 play in two acts by American playwright Bessie Breuer .
Martyn Pig is a thriller by Kevin Brooks , published on April 1 , 2002 by The Chicken House and aimed at teens and young adults .
Heaven Eyes is a young adult novel by award - winning author David Almond .
Reality and Dreams is a novel by Scottish author Muriel Spark , published in 1996 .
Titeuf is a Swiss comic series created by Zep in 1992 , which was adapted into a 2001 animated TV series and a 2011 film of the same name .
Gypsy in Amber is a 1971 mystery novel by Martin Cruz Smith as `` Martin Smith '' .
The Street Lawyer is a legal thriller novel by John Grisham .
Batman / The Spirit is a 2007 one - shot comic book written by Jeph Loeb with art by Darwyn Cooke and J. Bone .
The Blood Spilt ( Swedish : Det blod som spillts , 2004 ) is a crime novel by Swedish writer Åsa Larsson , second in the Rebecka Martinsson series .
The Wellstone is a 2003 hard science fiction novel by Wil McCarthy .
To Be the Man is an autobiographical book written by professional wrestler Ric Flair and Keith Elliot Greenberg , and edited by Mark Madden .
Marnie is an English novel first published in 1961 which was written by Winston Graham .
Inspector Canardo is a comics series created by the Belgian artist Benoît Sokal .
The Solar System and Back ( 1970 ) is a collection of science essays by Isaac Asimov .
Existentialism and Humanism ( French : L'existentialisme est un humanisme , `` Existentialism is a Humanism '' ) is a 1946 philosophical work by Jean - Paul Sartre .
A Short , Sharp Shock ( sometimes titled Short , Sharp Shock ) is a 1990 fantasy novel by Kim Stanley Robinson .
Another Bullshit Night in Suck City is a memoir by playwright and poet Nick Flynn , describing Flynn 's reunion with his estranged father , Jonathan , an alcoholic resident of the homeless shelter where Nick was a social worker in the late 1980s .
Bill , the Galactic Hero is a satirical science fiction novel by Harry Harrison , first published in 1965 .
Seinlanguage is a 1993 book written by Jerry Seinfeld .
A Fable is a 1954 novel written by the American author William Faulkner .
Doctor Gorpon is a 1991 three - issue comic book mini - series published by Malibu Comics , created by Marc Hansen .
Sum Practysis of Medecyne and other Short Works consists of a number of short poetic works customarily accredited to the Scottish poet Robert Henryson .
Liane the Wayfarer is the fourth short story in The Dying Earth ( 1950 ) , a collection of fantasy short stories by Jack Vance .
The Beardless Warriors is a 1960 World War II novel written by Richard Matheson , author of I Am Legend .
Drayman Henschel ( German : Führmann Henschell ) , also known as Carter Henschel , is an 1898 five - act naturalistic play by the German playwright Gerhart Hauptmann .
The Feather Men is a 1991 novel by the British adventurer Sir Ranulph Fiennes .
The Mathematical Magpie is an anthology published in 1962 , compiled by Clifton Fadiman as a companion volume to his Fantasia Mathematica ( 1958 ) .
Major Operation is a 1971 science fiction book by author James White and is the third volume in the Sector General series .
Engelsfors is a Swedish young adult fantasy trilogy written by Mats Strandberg and Sara Bergmark Elfgren .
Confession of a Murderer ( German : Beichte eines Mörders ) is a 1936 novel by the Austrian writer Joseph Roth .
The Wilderness Survival Guide is a supplement to the Advanced Dungeons and Dragons ( AD&D ) role - playing game , written by Kim Mohan and published by TSR , Inc. in 1986 ( ISBN 088038 - 291 - 0 ) .
The Bob Dylan Encyclopedia is a compendium of articles written by Michael Gray covering the life and work of Bob Dylan .
The Regeneration Trilogy is a series of three novels by Pat Barker on the subject of the First World War .
Gotham Underground is a nine - issue limited series from DC Comics , written by Frank Tieri , with art by Jim Califiore .
To Say Nothing of the Dog : or , How We Found the Bishop 's Bird Stump at Last is a 1997 comic science fiction novel by Connie Willis .
But Gentlemen Marry Brunettes is a 1927 novel written by Anita Loos .
The Lady Daffodilia is a children 's short story written by Evelyn Sharp and published in 1900 by John Lane .
Pierre ; or , The Ambiguities is a novel , the seventh book , by American writer Herman Melville , first published in New York in 1852 .
Invitation to a Beheading ( Russian : Приглашение на казнь , lit . Invitation to an execution ) is a novel by Russian American author Vladimir Nabokov .
Alongside Night is a dystopian novel by science fiction writer J. Neil Schulman intended to articulate the principles of Agorism , a political philosophy created by Samuel Edward Konkin III , to whom Schulman dedicated the work .
Zoobreak is a 2009 children 's novel by Gordon Korman and is the sequel to the 2008 book Swindle .
Simon the Coldheart is a novel by Georgette Heyer
A Time to Keep Silence ( 1953 ) is a travel book by British author Patrick Leigh Fermor .
`` The Cloak and the Staff '' is a science fiction novelette by Gordon R. Dickson .
Walt Disney 's Mickey Mouse ( also The Floyd Gottfredson Library ) is a series of books collecting the first 25 years of the 45-year span of work by Floyd Gottfredson on the daily Mickey Mouse comic strip .
`` They 're Made Out of Meat '' is a Nebula Award - nominated short story by Terry Bisson .
The Iron Dragon 's Daughter is a 1993 novel by writer Michael Swanwick that combines fantasy and science fiction .
The Book of Drugs is a 2012 memoir by musician and songwriter Mike Doughty .
De rerum natura ( Latin : ( deː ˈreːrũː naːˈtuːraː ) ; On the Nature of Things ) is a first - century BC didactic poem by the Roman poet and philosopher Lucretius ( c. 99 BC -- c. 55 BC ) with the goal of explaining Epicurean philosophy to a Roman audience .
Bug Jack Barron is a 1969 science fiction novel written by Norman Spinrad , and was nominated for the 1970 Hugo awards .
The Jubilee Book of Cricket is a classic work on Cricket by Prince K.S. Ranjitsinhji .
Silver Canyon is a novel written by Louis L'Amour set in south - central Utah Territory in 1881 .
Branded Outlaw is a Western adventure that takes place in the wild west of New Mexico , written by L. Ron Hubbard .
This High School Has Closets is a novel written by Robert Joseph Greene and published by Icon Empire Press in 2011 with a reprint the following year .
Sand Monkeys is a young adult novel by the Australian writer Joanne Horniman , who is known for novels centering on realistic depictions of people in unusual relationships .
Winner Take Nothing is a 1933 collection of short stories by Ernest Hemingway .
Mad Love Chase , is a manga by Kazusa Takashima .
The Moonlit Road is a gothic horror short story written by Ambrose Bierce .
Steps Along the Way is the spiritual autobiography of Diogenes Allen , professor emeritus at Princeton Theological Seminary .
Mr. Chas and Lisa Sue Meet the Pandas is a 1994 children 's book written by Fran Lebowitz with illustrations by Michael Graves .
Marhi Da Deeva ( Originally in Punjabi : ਮੜ੍ਹੀ ਦਾ ਦੀਵਾ , Literally meaning : The Lamp of the Tomb ) , sometimes spelled as Marhi Da Diva , is a 1964 Punjabi novel by Gurdial Singh .
The Whetstone of Witte is the shortened title of Robert Recorde 's mathematics book published in 1557 , the full title being The whetstone of witte , whiche is the seconde parte of Arithmetike : containyng thextraction of Rootes :
A Modest Proposal for Preventing the Children of Poor People From Being a Burthen to Their Parents or Country , and for Making Them Beneficial to the Publick , commonly referred to as A Modest Proposal , is a Juvenalian satirical essay written and published anonymously by Jonathan Swift in 1729 .
Tales of Nevèrÿon collects a preface ( to the entire series ) and five sword and sorcery stories by Samuel R. Delany ; and finally an appendix .
The Ambidextrous Universe is a popular science book by Martin Gardner ( 1914 - -2010 ) covering aspects of symmetry and asymmetry in human culture , science and the wider universe .
Les Thanatonautes ( English : The Thanatonauts ) is a 1994 science fiction novel by French writer Bernard Werber .
Mistral 's Daughter is a 1984 American television miniseries , adapted from Judith Krantz 's 1982 novel of the same name .
Castle Waiting is an Eisner Award winning comic book series created by Linda Medley .
`` I Ran Away with a Truck Driver '' is a 9-page romance comics story published in Teen - Age Romances , No . 23 by St. John Publishing in August 1952 with art ( and possibly script ) by Matt Baker .
The Fantastic Flying Journey ( ISBN 1850291055 ) is a children 's book written by Gerald Durrell .
The Haw Lantern ( 1987 ) is a collection of poems written by Irish poet Seamus Heaney , the recipient of the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1995 .
The Fat Years is a 2009 Chinese science fiction novel written by Chan Koonchung .
Rakas Henrietta ( Finnish : My Dear Henrietta ) is a historical novel by Finnish author Kaari Utrio .
The History of Human Marriage is an 1891 book about the history of human marriage by the Finnish philosopher Edvard Westermarck , a classic in its field .
Le Bal des Voleurs ( Thieves ' Carnival ) is a play written by French playwright Jean Anouilh , first staged at Théâtre des Arts , Paris on 17 August 1938 .
Night Lamp is a science fiction adventure novel by Jack Vance .
The Perilous Road is a novel , published in 1958 by William O. Steele .
Dimension of Miracles is a 1968 satirical with elements of absurdism science - fiction novel by Robert Sheckley .
The Tailor 's Needle ( 2009 ) is the debut novel of Indian writer Lakshmi Raj Sharma , who is a professor in the Department of English , University of Allahabad .
Dreams of Speaking is a 2006 novel by Australian author Gail Jones .
Being and Time ( German : Sein und Zeit ) is a 1927 book by the German philosopher Martin Heidegger .
The Abhidhammavatara was written in Pali , apparently in the 5th century , by the poet and scholar Buddhadatta in the region of the Kaveri River , in southern India '' .
The God Child is a crime novel by English author Paul Sayer published in 1996 .
In Praise of Cosmetics is the title given to Max Beerbohm 's article in the first edition of `` The Yellow Book '' published in 1894 .
Gender Blender ( ISBN 0 - 385 - 74696 - 2 , 2006 ) is a young adult novel written by Blake Nelson .
`` Raleigh was Right '' is a poem by William Carlos Williams , composed in response to the Elizabethan exchange between Christopher Marlowe , in `` The Passionate Shepherd to His Love '' , and Walter Raleigh , with `` The Nymph 's Reply '' .
Hungarian author Frigyes Karinthy 's fantastic novel Capillaria ( Hungarian : Capillária , 1921 ) , which depicts an undersea world inhabited exclusively by women , recounts , in a satirical vein reminiscent of the style of Jonathan Swift ( author of Gulliver 's Travels ) , the first time that men and women experience sex with one another .
Mr. Monk on the Couch is the twelfth novel written by Lee Goldberg to be based on the television series Monk .
Barbary Shore is Norman Mailer 's second published novel , written after Mailer 's great success with his 1948 debut The Naked and the Dead .
The Leavenworth Case ( 1878 ) , subtitled A Lawyer 's Story , is an American detective novel and the first novel by Anna Katharine Green .
Die Judenbuche ( The Jew 's Beech ) is a novella written by Annette von Droste - Hülshoff and first published in 1842 .
China Bomb is a near - future novel written by Richard Tregaskis .
The Sword of the Lady ( 2009 ) is an alternate history , post - apocalyptic novel by author S. M. Stirling .
The Good Soldiers ( 2009 ) is a non - fiction book about the 2007 troop surge in Iraq written by David Finkel , chronicling the deployment of 2nd Battalion , 16th Infantry Regiment of the 4th Infantry Brigade Combat Team , 1st Infantry Division , nicknamed `` Rangers '' , under the command of Lieutenant Colonel Ralph Kauzlarich .
A Room with a View is a 1908 novel by English writer E. M. Forster , about a young woman in the repressed culture of Edwardian era England .
Extreme Metaphors is a collection of interviews with the British writer J. G. Ballard , edited by Simon Sellars and Dan O'Hara , and published in 2012 .
Indian Ink is a 1995 play by Tom Stoppard based on his 1991 radio play In the Native State .
The Man Who Walked Through Time ( 1968 ) is Colin Fletcher 's chronicle of the first person to walk a continuous route through Grand Canyon National Park .
A Passage to India ( 1924 ) is a novel by English author E. M. Forster set against the backdrop of the British Raj and the Indian independence movement in the 1920s .
Quamquam pluries is an encyclical on Saint Joseph by Pope Leo XIII .
`` The Black Pits of Luna '' is a science fiction short story by Robert A. Heinlein about a Boy Scout on a trip to the Moon and his novel way of finding his lost brother .
Money and Friends is a 1991 Australian play written by David Williamson .
`` Till A’the Seas '' is a post - apocalyptic short story by American horror fiction writer H. P. Lovecraft and R. H. Barlow .
The Memoirs of an Amnesiac is the autobiography of composer , radio , and television personality Oscar Levant .
The Second Deadly Sin ( Swedish : Till offer åt Molok , 2011 ) is a crime novel by Swedish writer Åsa Larsson , fifth in the Rebecka Martinsson series .
The Sex Offender is a 1994 novel by Matthew Stadler .
The Wolfen ( 1978 ) is the debut novel of Whitley Strieber .
Three Tall Women is a play by Edward Albee , which won the 1994 Pulitzer Prize for Drama , Albee 's third .
Carnivorous Plants of Australia is a three - volume work on carnivorous plants by Allen Lowrie .
It 's Not All Shrovetide for the Cat ( Ne Vsyo Kotu Maslenitsa , Не всё коту масленица ) is a play by Alexander Ostrovsky written in 1871 and first published in the No.9 , September 1871 issue of Otechestvennye Zapiski .
Bhowani Junction is a 1954 novel by John Masters , which was the basis of a 1956 film starring Ava Gardner and Stewart Granger .
New Spring ( abbreviated as NS by fans ) is a prequel novel in the Wheel of Time fantasy series by American author Robert Jordan .
David Graham 's Down to a Sunless Sea ( 1979 ) is a post - apocalyptic novel about a planeload of people during and after a short nuclear war , set in a near - future world where the USA is critically short of oil .
Silver Birch , Blood Moon is an anthology of fantasy stories edited by Terri Windling and Ellen Datlow .
Do n't Make a Black Woman Take Off Her Earrings is a 2006 humor novel and New York Times bestseller by Tyler Perry and focuses on his character of Madea .
The Gnome King of Oz ( 1927 ) is the twenty - first in the series of Oz books created by L. Frank Baum and his successors , and the seventh by Ruth Plumly Thompson .
Csongor és Tünde is a Hungarian play , written by Mihály Vörösmarty .
Black Blossom ( Serbian : Црни цвет / Crni cvet ) is an epic high fantasy novel by Serbian writer Boban Knežević , published in 1993 .
Seven Types of Ambiguity is a work of literary criticism by William Empson which was first published in 1930 .
On the Peace ( Ancient Greek : Περὶ τῆς εἰρήνης ) is one of the most famous political orations of the prominent Athenian statesman and orator Demosthenes .
Streams of Silver is the second book in The Icewind Dale Trilogy , written by R. A. Salvatore .
The Structure of Liberty is a book by legal theorist Randy Barnett which offers a libertarian theory of law and politics .
Asia Overland by Mark Elliott and Wil Klass was an idiosyncratic book of the 1990s which developed a minor cult following amongst backpackers in Asia and the former Soviet Union .
Crooked Zebra is a 2004 novel by former University of Texas college basketball coach Bob Weltlich .
The Loving Spirit was the first novel of Daphne du Maurier and was published in 1931 by William Heinemann .
The Glorious Cause is a historical novel by author Jeff Shaara , a sequel to Rise to Rebellion and the conclusion to Shaara 's retelling of the American Revolution .
Dubin 's Lives is the seventh published novel by the American writer Bernard Malamud .
Back Story is a crime novel by Robert B. Parker , the 30th novel in his Spenser series .
All Time Top 1000 Albums is a book by Colin Larkin , creator and editor of the Encyclopedia of Popular Music .
Age of Science ( 2005 ) is a book about the relationship between Islam and science in Age of Science by author and Egyptian - American scientist , and the winner of the 1999 Nobel Prize in Chemistry Ahmed Zewail .
The Sleeping and the Dead is an anthology of Fantasy and Horror stories edited by August Derleth .
The Giraffe and the Pelly and Me is a 1985 children 's book written by Roald Dahl and illustrated by Quentin Blake .
Sherlock Holmes and the Railway Maniac is a Sherlock Holmes pastiche novel by Barrie Roberts which pits Sherlock Holmes against an anarchist who is bombing trains .
Ankare ( lit . Anchors ) is the seventh novel by Swedish author Klas Östergren .
Mendel Gdański a short story by Polish poet and short - story writer Maria Konopnicka published for the first time in 1890 in the Przegląd Literacki magazine .
The Dead Sea Scrolls Deception ( 1991 , ISBN 0 - 671 - 73454 - 7 ) is a book by authors Michael Baigent and Richard Leigh .
The Last Fine Time is a 1991 book by American author Verlyn Klinkenborg about a blue collar Polish - American bar in Buffalo , New York , inherited by his father - in - law in 1947 .
The Contortionist 's Handbook is the debut novel by novelist Craig Clevenger .
`` The Man on the Threshold '' ( original Spanish title `` El Hombre en el Umbral '' ) is a short story by Argentinian writer Jorge Luis Borges .
The Murder Book is a mystery novel by American author Jonathan Kellerman .
Cally 's War is a novel by John Ringo and Julie Cochrane , and is part of the Legacy of the Aldenata series .
The Mystery of the Clockwork Sparrow is the debut novel of British children 's author Katherine Woodfine , initially published by Egmont Publishing in June 2015 .
A God Strolling in the Cool of the Evening ( Portuguese : Um Deus Passeando Pela Brisa da Tarde ) is a historical novel by the Portuguese writer Mario de Carvalho , set in the Roman province of Lusitania during the reign of Roman Emperor Commodus .
The Sons of Avalon Saga is a series of Arthurian Legend novels , by American novelist , Dee Marie .
Maybe the Moon is a 1992 novel written by San Francisco novelist Armistead Maupin .
The Original of Laura is the incomplete novel by Vladimir Nabokov , which he was writing at the time of his death in 1977 .
Voice of the Whirlwind is a 1987 cyberpunk science fiction novel by Walter Jon Williams .
The Physick Book of Deliverance Dane is the first novel written by Katherine Howe , published by VOICE , an imprint of Hyperion ( publisher ) .
Flambard 's Confession is an historical novel written by the American author Marilyn Durham .
Goals in the Air is a 1972 children 's novel by prolific British author Michael Hardcastle .
The Rise of Silas Lapham is a realist novel by William Dean Howells published in 1885 .
The White Doe or The Doe in the Woods is a French literary fairy tale written by Madame d'Aulnoy .
The Stars Look Down is a 1935 novel by A. J. Cronin which chronicles various injustices in an English coal mining community .
Histoire naturelle des poissons is a 22-volume treatment of ichthyology published in 1828 - 1849 by the French savant Georges Cuvier ( 1769 - 1832 ) and his student and successor Achille Valenciennes ( 1794 - 1865 ) .
Girls Forever Brave and True ( also known as Girls No More ) is a 1986 fiction novel written by Caryl Rivers .
Death of a Train is a crime novel by Freeman Wills Crofts , published in 1946 .
Expedition Venus is a juvenile science fiction novel , the fifth in Hugh Walters ' Chris Godfrey of U.N.E.X.A. series .
The Eternal Lover is an Edgar Rice Burroughs fantasy - adventure novel .
Agésilas is a play written by Pierre Corneille and published in 1666 .
Eve 's Ransom is a novel by George Gissing , first published in 1895 as a serialisation in the Illustrated London News .
Archer at Large is an omnibus of Ross Macdonald 's Lew Archer novels , first published by Knopf in 1970 .
Last of the Amazons is a novel by Steven Pressfield that recounts the legend of Theseus and the Amazons , set before the threshold of recorded history , a generation before the Trojan War .
The Man Who Won the War ( 1936 ) is a short story by Robert Buckner .
88 Poems is a book of the collected poetry of author Ernest Hemingway , published in 1979 .
Lords of the Rim is a book written by American historian Sterling Seagrave .
Sister Pelagia is the heroine of a trilogy of mystery novels by Boris Akunin .
Bodyguard of Lies is a 1975 non - fiction book written by Anthony Cave Brown , his first major historical work .
So Vile a Sin is an original novel written by Ben Aaronovitch & Kate Orman and based on the long - running British science fiction television series Doctor Who .
69 Things to Do with a Dead Princess is an experimental novel by the British writer Stewart Home , first published by Canongate in 2002 .
The Root Cellar is a children 's historical novel by Janet Lunn that is set in the 1980s , although much of the action takes place in the 1860s .
The Grand Wheel is the eighth science fiction novel by Barrington J. Bayley .
Until I Find You ( 2005 ) is the 11th published novel by John Irving .
The Metamorphoses of Apuleius -- which St. Augustine referred to as The Golden Ass ( Asinus aureus ) -- is the only Ancient Roman novel in Latin to survive in its entirety .
Super - Cannes is a novel by the British author J. G. Ballard , published in 2000 .
A New Era of Thought is a non - fiction work written by Charles Howard Hinton , was published in 1888 and reprinted in 1900 by Swan Sonnenschein & Co. Ltd. , London .
`` Born of Man and Woman '' is a science fiction short story by American writer Richard Matheson , originally published in 1950 in The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction .
The Halfling 's Gem is the third book in The Icewind Dale Trilogy , written by R. A. Salvatore .
Fields , Factories and Workshops : or Industry Combined with Agriculture and Brain Work with Manual Work ( Russian : Поля , фабрики и мастерские ) is a landmark anarchist text by Peter Kropotkin , and arguably one of the most influential and positive statements of the anarchist political philosophy .
Episodes of the Cuban Revolutionary War also titled Reminiscences of the Cuban Revolutionary War is an autobiographical book by Marxist revolutionary Che Guevara about his experiences during the Cuban Revolution ( 1956 - 1958 ) to overthrow the dictatorship of Fulgencio Batista .
`` Lips to Lips '' is a short story written in Russian by Vladimir Nabokov in Berlin in or about 1931 .
The Word of a Gentleman ( 1981 ) ( later retitled Undercut ) was the third of five novels written by Peter Niesewand , the South African journalist who spent 73 days in solitary confinement for his coverage of Ian Smith 's government in Rhodesia ( now Zimbabwe ) .
`` The Reluctant Orchid '' is a science fiction short story by Arthur C. Clarke , first published in 1956 , and later anthologized in Tales from the White Hart .
Pubis Angelical is a 1979 novel by acclaimed Argentine novelist Manuel Puig .
Dirty Politics , subtitled `` How attack politics is poisoning New Zealand 's political environment '' , is a book by Nicky Hager published in August 2014 .
Polonia sive de situ , populis , moribus , magistratibus et Republica regni Polonici libri duo is a book by Marcin Kromer , first published in Cologne in 1577 in Latin .
Mad Toy ( original title : El juguete rabioso : `` The rabid toy '' ) is the first novel of Argentinean author Roberto Arlt .
Lectures on Aesthetics ( LA ; German : Vorlesungen über die Ästhetik ) is a compilation of notes from university lectures on aesthetics given by Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel in Heidelberg in 1818 and in Berlin in 1820/21 , 1823 , 1826 and 1828/29 .
Fengsu Tongyi ( Chinese : 風俗通義 ; literally : `` Comprehensive Meaning of Customs and Habits '' ) , also known as Fengsu Tong , is a book written about 195 AD by Ying Shao , who lived during the later Eastern Han period .
`` Letter to a Priest '' ( French : Lettre à un religieux ) is a letter containing thirty - five , `` expressions of opinion on matters concerning Catholic faith , dogma and institutions '' , by the French religious and social philosopher and mystic Simone Weil .
The 3rd edition Draconomicon was designed by Andy Collins , Skip Williams , and James Wyatt , and published in November 2003 .

Attack of the Mutant Underwear is a 2003 novel by children 's author Tom Birdseye .
How to Take Possession of the Blessing is a 1987 book written by Romildo Ribeiro Soares .
Salem Falls is a 2001 novel by Jodi Picoult about what happens to a person when he is given a label and not allowed to escape it .
With Fire and Sword ( Polish : Ogniem i mieczem ) is a historical novel by the Polish author Henryk Sienkiewicz , published in 1884 .
The Lesson of the Master is a novella written by Henry James , originally published in 1888 .
Killing Aurora is a novel by Helen Barnes about a girl with anorexia .
The Gun Seller ( 1996 ) is the first novel by English actor , musician , comedian , and writer Hugh Laurie .
Encyclopedia of American Religions , renamed Melton 's Encyclopedia of American Religions in the eighth edition , is a reference book by J. Gordon Melton first published in 1978 , by Consortium Books , A McGrath publishing company .
Starship Troupers is a science fiction series of novels by American author Christopher Stasheff .
Night Chills is a suspense novel by best - selling author Dean Koontz originally published in 1976 .
Peveril of the Peak ( 1823 ) is the longest novel by Sir Walter Scott .
`` Falling Onto Mars '' is a science fiction short story written in 2002 by Geoffrey A. Landis .
A Grave Talent ( 1993 ) is the first book in Laurie R. King 's Kate Martinelli series .
A Thousand Lies is a novel by British crime writer Laura Wilson , first published in 2006 .
Coelebs in Search of a Wife ( 1809 ) is a novel by the British Christian moralist Hannah More .
Sylvia 's Lovers ( 1863 ) is a novel written by Elizabeth Gaskell , which she called `` the saddest story I ever wrote '' .
The Devil 's Dictionary is a satirical dictionary written by American journalist and author Ambrose Bierce .
The Cageworld series is a science fiction series by Colin Kapp which takes place in a distant future where humanity lives on nested Dyson spheres .
Sandworms of Dune is the second of two novels written by Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson to conclude Frank Herbert 's original Dune series of novels based on notes left behind by Frank Herbert for Dune 7 , his own planned seventh novel in the Dune series .
Anne of the Island is the third book in the Anne of Green Gables series , written by Lucy Maud Montgomery about Anne Shirley .
Blood 's a Rover is a 2009 crime fiction novel by American author James Ellroy .
A Drunken Dream and Other Stories is a Japanese manga anthology written and illustrated by Moto Hagio , collecting a variety of her short stories originally from 1970 - -2007 .
Platero is a little donkey , main character of Platero y yo ( Spanish for Platero and I ) , one of Juan Ramón Jiménez 's most popular works .
Grantville Gazette II is the third collaborative anthology published in print set in the 1632-verse shared universe in what is best regarded as a canonical sub - series of the popular alternate history that began with the February 2000 publication of the hardcover novel 1632 by author - historian Eric Flint .
The Clayhanger Family is a series of novels by Arnold Bennett , published between 1910 and 1918 .
Rabble Starkey ( 1987 ) is a novel by Lois Lowry .
El licenciado Vidriera ( `` The Lawyer of Glass '' ) is a short story written by Miguel de Cervantes and included in his Novelas ejemplares , first published in 1613 .
Mookajjiya Kanasugalu ( English : Dreams of Mookajji ) is a 1968 Kannada epic novel written by K. Shivaram Karanth .
Welcome to Our Hillbrow , is a novel by South African novelist Phaswane Mpe which deals with issues of xenophobia , AIDS , tradition , and inner city status in the Hillbrow neighborhood of post - apartheid Johannesburg .
Young Hearts Crying is the penultimate novel of American writer Richard Yates .
Epitaph for George Dillon is an early John Osborne play , one of two he wrote in collaboration with Anthony Creighton ( the other is Personal Enemy ) .
Tales of the Crusaders is a series of two historical novels by Sir Walter Scott released in 1825 :
The Killings at Badger 's Drift ( 1987 ) is a mystery novel by English writer Caroline Graham , the first in her Chief Inspector Barnaby series .
Commentarii de Bello Civili ( Commentaries on the Civil War ) , or Bellum Civile , is an account written by Julius Caesar of his war against Gnaeus Pompeius and the Senate .
The Dragon Lord is a historical fantasy or sword and sorcery novel by American writer David Drake .
The Last Sin Eater is a 1998 Christian book by the American author Francine Rivers .
Multidimensional Measurement of Religiousness / Spirituality for Use in Health Research is a report , originally published in 1999 , by a Fetzer Institute / National Institute on Aging working group on the measurement of religion and spirituality .
The Bellmaker is a fantasy novel by Brian Jacques , published in 1994 .
Lemonade Mouth is a young adult novel by Mark Peter Hughes , published in 2007 by Delacorte Press .
Mengele Zoo is a novel from 1989 by the Norwegian author Gert Nygårdshaug .
The Brotherhood of Fear is a 1952 political novel by Robert Ardrey .
Starswarm is a 1998 science fiction novel by Jerry Pournelle .
The New Journalism is a 1973 anthology of journalism edited by Tom Wolfe and E. W. Johnson .
The Gospel According to Jesus Christ ( original title : O Evangelho Segundo Jesus Cristo , 1991 ) is a novel by the Portuguese author José Saramago .
The Aesthetics of Resistance ( German : Die Ästhetik des Widerstands , 1975 - 1981 ) is a three - volume novel by the German - born playwright , novelist , filmmaker , and painter Peter Weiss .
Melmoth the Wanderer is an 1820 Gothic novel by Irish playwright , novelist and clergyman Charles Maturin .
Driftless a winner of the Milkweed Editions National Fiction Prize , is a novel by David Rhodes that was published in 2008 .
The Bachman Books is a collection of short novels by Stephen King published under the pseudonym Richard Bachman between 1977 and 1982 .
First Lord 's Fury is a 2009 high fantasy novel by Jim Butcher .
The Stars Are Ours ! is a 1954 science fiction novel written by Andre Norton .
The Enemies of Jupiter is a children 's historical novel by Caroline Lawrence published on 6 November 2003 by Orion Books .
Ravelstein is Saul Bellow 's final novel .
Aunt Jane 's Nieces and Uncle John is a young - adult novel written by L. Frank Baum , famous as the creator of the Land of Oz . It is the sixth volume in the ten - book series Aunt Jane 's Nieces , Baum 's greatest commercial success after the Oz books themselves .
A Tale of Time City was first published in 1987 by British author Diana Wynne Jones .
Tomorrow in the Battle Think on Me ( Spanish : Mañana en la batalla piensa en mí ) by Javier Marías was first published in 1994 .
What Did the Biblical Writers Know and When Did They Know It ? is a book by biblical scholar and archaeologist William G. Dever detailing his response to the claims of minimalists to the historicity and value of the Hebrew Bible .
Beowulf and the Critics by J. R. R. Tolkien is a book edited by Michael D. C. Drout that presents scholarly editions of the two manuscript versions of Tolkien 's essays or lecture series `` Beowulf and the Critics '' , which served as the basis for the much shorter 1936 lecture `` Beowulf :
Etymologiae ( Latin for `` The Etymologies '' ) , also known as the Origines ( `` Origins '' ) and usually abbreviated Orig . , is an etymological encyclopedia compiled by Isidore of Seville ( c. 560 - -636 ) towards the end of his life .
Duncton Wood is the title of the first novel by author William Horwood , as well as a six - volume fantasy series to which it was later extended .
C Primer Plus ( currently in the 6th Edition ) is a book by Stephen Prata meant for beginners to the C programming language .
Ghostgirl is the debut novel from author and filmmaker Tonya Hurley .
The Kidnapping of Kensington is a children 's novel by Richard Hough under the pen name of Bruce Carter .
Cloud of Sparrows ( 2002 ) is the first historic novel by author Takashi Matsuoka featuring the struggle of Genji , the young Great Lord of Akaoka , in the year 1861 .
Gaston de Blondeville is a Gothic novel by noted English author Ann Radcliffe , published posthumously in 1826 , three years after Radcliffe 's death .
The Case of Lady Sannox is a short story by Sir Arthur Conan - Doyle that features an arrogant surgeon , Douglas Stone , who is in love with the married Lady Sannox , one of the most beautiful women in London .
Men Are from Mars , Women Are from Venus ( 1993 ) is a book written by an American author and relationship counselor John Gray .
The False Inspector Dew is a humorous crime novel by Peter Lovesey .
The King 's Curse is a 2014 historical novel by Philippa Gregory , part of her series The Cousins ' War .
The Basic Eight is the debut novel by author Daniel Handler published in 1998 .
Le Père de famille ( English : The Father of the family ) is a 1758 play by Denis Diderot .
The Sex Magicians is the first novel by Robert Anton Wilson , released in 1973 .
Darkness Under the Sun is a 2010 novella by Dean Koontz which is related to and appeared in print as part of What the Night Knows .
`` Of Missing Persons '' is a 1955 science fiction short story by Jack Finney , which describes a burned - out bank teller named Charley Ewell living in 1955 New York City who receives a chance to emigrate from Earth to Verna , a lush , earthlike planet light - years away .
Love , Loss , and What I Wore is a play written by Nora and Delia Ephron based on the 1995 book of the same name by Ilene Beckerman .
The Mask of Loki ( 1990 ) is an epic science fiction / fantasy novel by Roger Zelazny and Thomas T. Thomas , detailing a centuries long struggle between the avatars of Loki and Ahriman .
Sunset Over Chocolate Mountains is the critically acclaimed first novel by English author Susan Elderkin published by Fourth Estate , It won a Betty Trask Award in 2000 .
Sofia Petrovna is a novella by Russian author Lydia Chukovskaya , written in the late 1930s in the Soviet Union .
Berömda män som varit i Sunne ( lit . Famous Men Who Have Visited Sunne ) is a 1998 novel by Swedish author Göran Tunström about Sunne .
The Last and the First is Ivy Compton - Burnett 's posthumous novel , published in 1971 , two years after her death .
Skybowl is a 1994 fantasy novel written by author Melanie Rawn .
The Fox and the Grapes is one of the Aesop 's fables , numbered 15 in the Perry Index .
Lyra 's Oxford is a short book by Philip Pullman depicting an episode involving the heroine of His Dark Materials , Pullman 's best - selling trilogy .
Pride of Baghdad is a graphic novel written by Brian K. Vaughan and illustrated by Niko Henrichon released by DC Comics ' Vertigo imprint on September 13 , 2006 .
Under the Frog is British - born Hungarian writer Tibor Fischer 's debut novel , it was published in 1992 .
The Tough Guide To Fantasyland is a nonfiction book by the British author Diana Wynne Jones that humorously examines the common tropes of a broad swathe of fantasy fiction .
Children of Dune is a 1976 science fiction novel by Frank Herbert , the third in his Dune series of six novels .
The Cruelest Month , by Louise Penny , is the third novel in the Three Pines Mysteries series , which feature Inspector Armand Gamache .
A Prisoner of Birth is a mystery novel by English author Jeffrey Archer , first published on 6 March 2008 by Macmillan .
Jim Button and Luke the Engine Driver ( original title : Jim Knopf und Lukas der Lokomotivführer ) is a German children 's novel written by Michael Ende .
Knight Life ( ISBN 0 - 441 - 01077 - 6 ) , is an Arthurian fantasy novel by Peter David .
Stuck in Fast Forward , also known as The Hunger of Time in an expanded edition , is a 1999 young - adult science fiction novel by Damien Broderick & Rory Barnes .
His at Night is a historical romance by Sherry Thomas .
A Protégée of the Mistress ( Vospitannitsa , Воспитанница ; also , The Ward Girl ) is a play by Alexander Ostrovsky , first published in the No.1 , January 1859 issue of Biblioteka Dlya Chteniya .
Heirs of Empire is a 1996 military science fiction novel by David Weber .
Runemarks is a 2007 fantasy novel by Joanne Harris .
Mr Noon is an unfinished novel by the English writer , D. H. Lawrence .
Swastika Night is a futuristic novel by Katharine Burdekin , writing under the pseudonym Murray Constantine , first published in 1937 .
Tribes of Redwall Otters was published in 2002 as an accessory to the Redwall series by Brian Jacques .
Hope for the Flowers is an allegorical novel by Trina Paulus .
Biloxi Blues is a semi - autobiographical play by Neil Simon .
Dandelion Fire is a 2009 children 's fantasy novel by N. D. Wilson .
Written by the Dutch philosopher Baruch Spinoza , the Tractatus Theologico - Politicus or Theologico - Political Treatise was one of the most controversial texts of the early modern period .
Exploding Head is the second album from the noise rock band A Place to Bury Strangers .
The Angel 's Game ( El juego del ángel , 2008 ) is a prequel to 2001 's The Shadow of the Wind by Spanish author Carlos Ruiz Zafón .
Joey Pigza Loses Control , is a Newbery Honor book by Jack Gantos and is the sequel to Joey Pigza Swallowed the Key .
M or F ? is a 2005 novel for young adults co - written by Lisa Papademetriou and Chris Tebbetts .
A Mouthful of Birds is a 1986 play with dance by Caryl Churchill and David Lan , with choreography by Ian Spink .
The Trials of Rumpole is a collection of short stories by John Mortimer adapted from scripts for his TV series about Horace Rumpole .
Anna Mercury is a comic book limited series created by Warren Ellis , published by Avatar Press , with art by Facundo Percio .
The Third Option is Vince Flynn 's third novel , and the 2nd to feature Mitch Rapp , an American agent that works for the CIA as an operative for a covert counterterrorism unit called the `` Orion Team . ''
Sleepwalking Land ( in Portuguese : Terra Sonâmbula ) is a novel written by Mia Couto , a Mozambican writer , first published in Portuguese in 1992 and translated into English by David Brookshaw in 2006 .
Places I Never Meant to Be is a book edited by Judy Blume and first published in 1999 .
Death of a Red Heroine is a mystery novel written by Qiu Xiaolong and published in English in the year 2000 .
The Turner Diaries is a 1978 novel by William Luther Pierce ( founder of the white nationalist organization National Alliance ) , published under the pseudonym `` Andrew Macdonald '' .
Vienna Prelude is the first book of the Zion Covenant historical fiction series by Bodie and Brock Thoene .
The Yemassee : a romance of Carolina is an 1835 novel by William Gilmore Simms that was a popular bestseller of its time , and Simms ' best known novel .
The Counterfeit Man is a collection of science fiction short stories by Alan E. Nourse , published in 1963 by David McKay .
Stranger with My Face is a young - adult horror novel by Lois Duncan , first published in 1981 .
L'Esclusa ( Italian pronunciation : ( leˈskluːza ) ) ( English : The Excluded Woman ) was Luigi Pirandello 's first novel .
Through Black Spruce is a novel by Canadian writer Joseph Boyden , published in 2008 by Viking Press .
The Best of Science Fiction , published in 1946 , is the first of more than forty science fiction anthologies edited by Groff Conklin .
Medieval Children is a book on the history of childhood written by English historian Nicholas Orme in 2001 .
A Conspiracy of Friends is the third online novel by Alexander McCall Smith , author of the The No . 1 Ladies ' Detective Agency series .
`` On Exactitude in Science '' or `` On Rigor in Science '' ( the original Spanish - language title is `` Del rigor en la ciencia '' ) is a one - paragraph short story by Jorge Luis Borges , about the map - territory relation , written in the form of a literary forgery .
Leaving Fishers ( 1997 ) is a young adult novel written by Margaret Peterson Haddix centering on a high school girl , Dorry Stevens , and her descent into and escape from a cult called The Fishers of Men .
Manituana is a novel by Wu Ming first published in Italian in 2007 .
The original Arms and Equipment Guide was designed by Grant Boucher , Troy Christensen , Jon Pickens , John Terra , and Scott Davis .
The Demon Breed is a 1968 science fiction novel by James H. Schmitz , originally serialized in Analog in a shorter form as `` The Tuvela '' .
The Inheritance of Loss is the second novel by Indian author Kiran Desai .
Bats at the Beach is a NY Times bestselling picture book by Brian Lies .
Monster Love is the debut novel of English author Carol Topolski , published in 2008 by Fig Tree , an imprint of Penguin and was nominated for the Orange Prize for Fiction .
Neonomicon is a four - issue comic book limited series written by Alan Moore and illustrated by Jacen Burrows , published by American company Avatar Press in 2010 .
Finity 's End is a science fiction novel written by the American science fiction and fantasy author C. J. Cherryh .
Prefaces ( Danish : Forord ) is a book by Søren Kierkegaard published under the pseudonym Nicolaus Notabene .
Land of Unlikeness , Robert Lowell 's first book of poetry , was published in 1944 in a limited edition of two hundred and fifty copies by Harry Duncan at the Cummington Press .
Mr. Munchausen is a novel by John Kendrick Bangs , written in the style that has become known as Bangsian fantasy as well as being one of the main inspirations of a style known as Equestria Fantasy .
Child of Fortune is a 1985 science fiction novel by the American author Norman Spinrad .
King Solomon 's Carpet ( 1991 ) is a novel by Barbara Vine , pseudonym of Ruth Rendell .
Bring Up the Bodies is a historical novel by Hilary Mantel and sequel to her award - winning Wolf Hall .
Agent of Vega is a science fiction novel by James H. Schmitz , 1960 .
The Art of the Faker is an influential 1959 book on art forgery by Frank Arnau .
The Two - Bear Mambo is a suspense\crime novel written by American author Joe R. Lansdale .
The Philebus ( /fɪˈliːbəs/ ; occasionally given as Philebos ; Greek : Φίληβος ) , is one of the surviving Socratic dialogues written in the 4th century BC by the ancient Greek philosopher Plato .
The School of Fear is the fifth novel by Jude Watson in the Star Wars Jedi Quest book series .
Methoden der mathematischen Physik ( Methods of Mathematical Physics ) is a 1924 book , in two volumes totalling around 1000 pages , published under the names of David Hilbert and Richard Courant .
Of True Religion , Heresy , Schism , Toleration ; and what best means may be used against the Growth of Popery is the title of a polemical tract against the popery of the Roman Catholic Church written by John Milton which was published in London in 1673 .
The Golden Book of Springfield is a mystic , utopian book by American poet Vachel Lindsay .
Darwin 's Radio is a 1999 science fiction novel by Greg Bear .
Neviditelný ( Jaroslav Havlíček ) is a Czech novel by Jaroslav Havlíček .
La Légende des siècles ( The Legend of the Ages ) is a collection of poems by Victor Hugo , conceived as an immense depiction of the history and evolution of humanity .
Vanilla Ride is a crime fiction novel written by American author Joe R. Lansdale .
Venture to the Moon is a group of six linked science fiction short stories by Arthur C. Clarke .
A Kind of Anger is a novel by British thriller writer Eric Ambler , first published in 1964 .
Beyond Doubt is a science fiction story written by Robert A. Heinlein , originally printed in Astonishing Stories in April 1941 under the pen name `` Lyle Monroe and Elma Wentz '' .
Jonathan Troy ( 1954 ) was Edward Abbey 's first published novel , as detailed in James M. Cahalan 's biography of Abbey .
Milrose Munce and the Den of Professional Help is a 2007 young adult novel by Douglas Anthony Cooper and is his first book in the genre .
`` The Commuter '' is a science - fiction short story by American writer Philip K. Dick .
The Keeping Place is a science fiction novel by Isobelle Carmody , set in a post apocalyptic world .
The Homecoming of Beorhtnoth Beorhthelm 's Son is the title of a work by J. R. R. Tolkien that was originally published in 1953 in volume 6 of the scholarly journal Essays and Studies by Members of the English Association , and later republished in 1966 in The Tolkien Reader .
The Cat 's Table is a novel by Canadian author Michael Ondaatje first published in 2011 .
Diary of a Wombat is a 2002 award - winning picture book written by Jackie French and illustrated by Bruce Whatley .
The Ramsay Scallop is a young adult historical romance written by Frances Temple .
The Falling Woman is a 1986 contemporary psychological fantasy novel by Pat Murphy .
The Candlemass Road is a historical novel from George MacDonald Fraser set in the time of the Border Reivers , a period Fraser had earlier written about in The Steel Bonnets .
Os Bruzundangas ( English : The Bruzundangas ) is a short story book written by Brazilian writer Lima Barreto .
Orion You Came and You Took All My Marbles is a 2010 mystery novel by Kira Henehan .
100 Greatest African Americans is a biographical dictionary of the one hundred historically greatest Black Americans ( in no particular order ; that is , they are not ranked ) , as assessed by Molefi Kete Asante in 2002 .
Hozuki 's Coolheadedness , originally known as Hōzuki no Reitetsu ( Japanese : 鬼灯の冷徹 ) , is a Japanese manga series written and illustrated by Natsumi Eguchi .
Paintings of Abanindranath Tagore is a book on Abanindranath Tagore 's paintings by art historian R. Siva Kumar .
The Canticle of the Sun , also known as the Canticle of the Creatures or Laudes Creaturarum ( Praise of the Creatures ) , is a religious song composed by Saint Francis of Assisi .
The Ghost House is the fourth audio story in a series of ten audiobooks , written by Stephen Cole and is a spin - off from the British science fiction television series The Sarah Jane Adventures , itself a spin - off from Doctor Who .
The Dogs of Babel ( also known as Lorelei 's Secret in the UK ) is the debut novel of Carolyn Parkhurst .
The Godwhale is a science fiction novel by American novelist T. J. Bass , first published in 1974 .
A Legacy is a semi - autobiographical novel by Sybille Bedford first published in 1956 .
Dorian , an Imitation is a British novel by Will Self .
The Night Manager is an espionage / detective novel by John le Carré , published in 1993 .
Eleven Blue Men , and Other Narratives of Medical Detection is an award winning collection of twelve true short stories written by Berton Roueché and published in 1953 .
People of the Deer ( published in 1952 , revised in 1975 ) is Canadian author Farley Mowat 's first book , and brought him literary recognition .
The Bone Bed is novel by Patricia Cornwell .
No Crystal Stair is a novel , published in 1997 , by Canadian author Mairuth Sarsfield .
The Book of Salt is Vietnamese - American author Monique Truong 's first novel ; it presents a narrative through the eyes of Bình , a Vietnamese cook .
De Tranquillitate Animi ( On the tranquility of the mind ) is a Latin work by Seneca ( 4 BC--65 AD ) .
Common Grounds is a six - issue comic book limited series created by writer Troy Hickman and published by Top Cow Productions in 2004 .
The Seven Storey Mountain is the 1948 autobiography of Thomas Merton , a Trappist monk and a noted author of the 1940s , 1950s and 1960s .
The Shockwave Rider is a science fiction novel by John Brunner , originally published in 1975 .
Stand on Zanzibar is a dystopian New Wave science fiction novel written by John Brunner and first published in 1968 .
Boy Kills Man is 2004 novel by British novelist Matt Whyman about child assassins in Medellin , Colombia .
The Vikings at Helgeland ( Hærmændene paa Helgeland ) is Henrik Ibsen 's seventh play .
Un fil à la patte ( known in English as Cat Among the Pigeons or Love on the Rack ) is a French bedroom farce in three acts written by Georges Feydeau .
Blinky Bill is an anthropomorphic koala and children 's fictional character created by author and illustrator Dorothy Wall .
The Sign in Sidney Brustein 's Window is the second and last staged play by playwright Lorraine Hansberry , author of A Raisin in the Sun . The play is a story about a man named Sidney , his pitfalls within his personal life , and struggles in Bohemian culture .
The Moon by Night ( ISBN 0 - 374 - 35049 - 3 ) is the title of a young adult novel by Madeleine L'Engle .
The Threat Within by Jude Watson is the eighteenth and final book in the Jedi Apprentice series of young reader novels .
My Life in France is an autobiography by Julia Child , published in 2006 .
The Hunger and Other Stories is the first collection of short stories by Charles Beaumont , published in April 1957 .
Act Without Words I is a short play by Samuel Beckett .
These Happy Golden Years is an autobiographical children 's novel written by Laura Ingalls Wilder and published in 1943 , the eight of nine books in her Little House series -- although it originally ended the series .
Eclogue 4 , also known as the Fourth Eclogue is the name of a Latin poem by the Roman poet Virgil .
Heroes and Horrors is a collection of fantasy and horror short stories by Fritz Leiber , edited by Stuart David Schiff and illustrated by Tim Kirk .
The Runaway Sleigh Ride ! ( Swedish : Titta Madicken , det snöar ! ) is a 1983 Astrid Lindgren children 's book .
The Dead and the Gone is a young adult science fiction dystopian novel by Susan Beth Pfeffer .
Athalie is a 1691 play , the final tragedy of Jean Racine , and has been described as the masterpiece of `` one of the greatest literary artists known '' and the `` ripest work '' of Racine 's genius .
The Road of Dreams is a book of poetry by crime writer Agatha Christie .
The Summer Book ( in the original Swedish Sommarboken ) is a book written by Finnish author Tove Jansson in 1972 .
On the Shore of the Wide World is a play by English playwright Simon Stephens .
An Early Martyr and Other Poems is a book of poetry by the American poet William Carlos Williams .
Wayne of Gotham is a novel by Tracy Hickman and is about the fictional superhero Batman .
`` De Daumier - Smith 's Blue Period '' is a short story by J. D. Salinger , first published in the British journal Information World Review in 1952 .
Zak 's Lunch is a book written by Margie Palatini and Illustrated by Howard Fine .
Jungle Tales of Tarzan is a collection of twelve loosely connected short stories written by Edgar Rice Burroughs , comprising the sixth book in order of publication in his series about the title character Tarzan .
Solomon 's Song is the final novel in the Australian Trilogy by author Bryce Courtenay .
Everything You Always Wanted to Know About Sex * ( * But Were Afraid to Ask ) is a book ( 1969 , updated 1999 ) by U.S. physician David Reuben .
`` The Library of Babel '' ( Spanish : La biblioteca de Babel ) is a short story by Argentine author and librarian Jorge Luis Borges ( 1899 - -1986 ) , conceiving of a universe in the form of a vast library containing all possible 410-page books of a certain format and character set .
The Tao of Programming is a book written in 1987 by Geoffrey James .
The Bride of Lammermoor is a historical novel by Sir Walter Scott , published in 1819 .
The Psychology of Self - Esteem is a book by Nathaniel Branden , first published in 1969 .
At All Costs is American author David Weber 's eleventh Honor Harrington novel , first published in 2005 .
Lakota Woman is a memoir by Mary Brave Bird , formerly Mary Crow Dog , a Sicangu Lakota .
Orpheus with Clay Feet is a science fiction short story by Philip K. Dick originally published in 1964 in Escapade magazine .
The Confessions of Nat Turner is a 1967 Pulitzer Prize - winning novel by U.S. writer William Styron .
Rosshalde is a short novel by the German author Hermann Hesse .
Paths of Darkness is the New York Times best - selling series of novels chronicling adventures of the renegade drow elf character Drizzt Do'Urden written by R. A. Salvatore .
Beyond Reach is the sixth novel in the Grant County series by Karin Slaughter , originally published in 2007 .
`` The Black Stone '' is a classic short story by Robert E. Howard , first published in the November 1931 issue of Weird Tales .
`` Autofac '' is a 1955 science fiction short story by Philip K. Dick that features one of the earliest treatments ( and Dick 's second ) of self - replicating machines .
Asphodel , That Greeny Flower is a poem by American poet William Carlos Williams .
The Time of the Ghost is a supernatural English - language children 's novel by Diana Wynne Jones , published by Macmillan in 1981 .
The Mote in God 's Eye is a science fiction novel by American writers Larry Niven and Jerry Pournelle , first published in 1974 .
Power Without Glory is a 1950 novel written by Australian writer Frank Hardy .
Ecce and Old Earth is a 1991 science fiction novel by Jack Vance , the middle novel in the Cadwal Chronicles trilogy , set in Vance 's Gaean Reach .
A Married Man 's Story is an unfinished 1923 short story by Katherine Mansfield .
The Zendian problem was an exercise in communication intelligence operations ( mainly traffic analysis and cryptanalysis ) devised by Lambros D. Callimahos as part of an advanced course , CA-400 , that Callimahos taught to National Security Agency cryptanalysts starting in the 1950s .
Frontline Combat was an anthology war comic book written and edited by Harvey Kurtzman and published bi - monthly by EC Comics .
The Robert E. Howard Reader is a collection of essays on fantasy writer Robert E. Howard and his works , edited by Darrell Schweitzer .
Abkari is a 1988 Malayalam movie starring Mammootty and Ratheesh in the title roles .
Khullam Khulla Pyaar Karen ( Hindi : खुल्लम खुल्ला प्यार करें , Urdu : کھلم کھلا پیار کریں ) is a Bollywood movie starring Govinda and Preity Zinta .
Pest from the West is the first short subject starring American comedian Buster Keaton made for Columbia Pictures .
Girls of the Big House is a 1945 American drama film directed by George Archainbaud and starring Lynne Roberts , Virginia Christine and Marion Martin .
Midnight Garage ( simplified Chinese : 三更车库 ; traditional Chinese : 三更車庫 ; pinyin : Sāngēng Chēkù ) is a 2015 Chinese horror film directed and written by Zhou Yaowu and starring Alex Fong , Yoon So - yi and Gordon Lam .
They Still Call Me Bruce is a 1987 comedy action film starring Johnny Yune .
Fatty and Mabel at the San Diego Exposition is a 1915 American silent black - and - white short comedy film , directed by Fatty Arbuckle and starring Arbuckle and Mabel Normand .
Life Without George was a BBC comedy series written by Penny Croft and Val Hudson and starring Simon Cadell and Carol Royle , centred on a young woman 's struggle to adapt to life after being left by her partner ( the titular George ) .
Hiroshima mon amour concerns a series of conversations ( or one enormous conversation ) over a 36-hour long period between a French actress ( Emmanuelle Riva ) , referred to as Her , and a Japanese architect ( Eiji Okada ) , referred to as Him .
Flavor of Love is an American satire reality television dating game show starring Flavor Flav of the rap group Public Enemy .
Hired Wife is a 1940 romantic comedy film starring Rosalind Russell and Brian Aherne .
Farewell Performance is a 1963 British crime film directed by Robert Tronson and starring David Kernan , Frederick Jaeger and Delphi Lawrence .
The Far Paradise is a 1928 Australian silent film directed by Paulette McDonagh and starring Marie Lorraine the stage name of Isabel McDonagh .
Thaayillamal Naan Illai ( Tamil : தாய் இல்லாமல் நான் இல்லை ; English : I can not live without my mother ) is a 1979 Tamil language film starring Kamal Haasan , Sridevi , Major Sundarrajan and Jaiganesh in the lead roles with Rajnikanth and Nagesh in guest roles .
I Was a Communist for the FBI is a 1951 American film noir drama directed by Gordon Douglas , and featuring Frank Lovejoy , Dorothy Hart , Philip Carey , and James Millican .
Battling with Buffalo Bill is a 1931 American Pre - Code Western serial film directed by Ray Taylor and starring Tom Tyler , Lucile Browne , William Desmond , Rex Bell , and Francis Ford .
The Affairs of Annabel is a 1938 comedy starring Lucille Ball and Jack Oakie .
Saxondale is a British television situation comedy programme , starring Steve Coogan and co - written by Steve Coogan and Neil Maclennan .
Sibs starred veteran actress Marsha Mason as Nora Ruscio , a successful accountant and Alex Rocco as her long - suffering husband , Howie .
The Criminal is a 1960 British drama film produced by Nat Cohen and directed by Joseph Losey , starring Stanley Baker , Sam Wanamaker and Jill Bennett .

Something for Everyone is a black comedy starring Angela Lansbury , Michael York , Anthony Higgins , and Jane Carr .

Wild Spur ( 64 ° 42′S 62 ° 32′W ) is a spur extending from Pulfrich Peak to the west side of Arctowski Peninsula , on the west coast of Graham Land in Antarctica .
Ob ' Passage ( 66 ° 33′S 93 ° 1′E ) is a passage 0.4 nautical miles ( 0.7 km ) wide between Khmary Island and Mabus Point on the coast of Antarctica .
The Dione Nunataks ( 71 ° 56′S 69 ° 6′W ) are rock exposures at the head of Saturn Glacier , 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) west of Deimos Ridge in the southeastern part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Exum Glacier ( 73 ° 30′S 94 ° 14′W ) is a small glacier flowing north between Hughes Point and Bonnabeau Dome , in the Jones Mountains of Antarctica .
Bizone Rock ( Bulgarian : скала Бизоне , `` Skala Bizone '' \'ska - la bi-'zo - ne\ ) is the rock off Snow Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica extending 120 m in southeast - northwest direction and 100 m wide .
Guépratte Island is an ice - covered island 2.8 km ( 1.7 mi ) long , lying between Anvers Island and Brabant Island at the east side of the entrance to Fournier Bay , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
The Lance Rocks ( 82 ° 52′S 48 ° 19′W ) are two rocks lying together at the northeast end of Crouse Spur in the Forrestal Range , Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Kita - karamete Rock ( 69 ° 4′S 35 ° 23′E ) is a rock situated 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) north of Minami - karamete Rock in the eastern part of Riiser - Larsen Peninsula , Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Laussedat Heights ( 64 ° 47′S 62 ° 30′W ) are a series of elevations extending eastward for 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) in the southwest part of Arctowski Peninsula , on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Plummer Glacier ( 79 ° 58′S 81 ° 30′W ) is a short glacier descending east through the Enterprise Hills to the north of Lippert Peak and the Douglas Peaks , in the Heritage Range in Antarctica .
Lemaire Channel is a strait off Antarctica , between Kiev Peninsula in the mainland 's Graham Land and Booth Island .
The Haskard Highlands ( 80 ° 30′S 29 ° 15′W ) are a range of peaks and ridges between Blaiklock Glacier and Stratton Glacier in the northwest of the Shackleton Range , Antarctica , rising to 1,210 metres ( 3,970 ft ) at Mount Weston and including features between Mount Provender and Pointer Nunatak .
Mount J. J. Thomson ( 77 ° 41′19``S 162 ° 15′40''E ) is a prominent hump - shaped peak along the north wall of Taylor Valley , standing above Lake Bonney , between Rhone Glacier and Matterhorn Glacier , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Edwards Pillar ( 73 ° 5′S 66 ° 20′E ) is a large rock pillar on the western face of Mount Stinear in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Mericle Rock ( 73 ° 39′S 163 ° 15′E ) is a nunatak in the middle of Campbell Glacier , approximately 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) from its head , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Lhasa Nunatak ( 85 ° 7′S 171 ° 18′E ) is a narrow rock ridge , 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) long , trending in a northwest -- southeast direction between Snakeskin Glacier and Jensen Glacier , to the east of the Supporters Range , Antarctica .
The Gould Nunataks ( 66 ° 30′S 51 ° 42′E ) are a small group of nunataks about 18 nautical miles ( 33 km ) southeast of Mount Biscoe in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Isbul Point ( Bulgarian : нос Исбул , `` Nos Isbul '' \'nos is-'bul\ ) is a narrow rocky point projecting 600 m from the coast of Ray Promontory into Svishtov Cove in the northwest extremity of Byers Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Alph River is a small river of Antarctica , running into Walcott Bay , Victoria Land .
Mount Eyskens ( 71 ° 32′S 35 ° 36′E ) is a large rock and ice massif rising to 2,300 metres ( 7,500 ft ) next northward of Mount Derom in the Queen Fabiola Mountains of Antarctica .
Marsh Spur ( 65 ° 53′S 62 ° 38′W ) is a spur in the eastern Voden Heights about 4.5 nautical miles ( 8 km ) south of Bildad Peak and 4.5 nautical miles west of Scar Inlet on the east side of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Kosar Point ( 71 ° 8′S 73 ° 7′W ) is a snow - covered headland forming the westernmost extremity of the Eroica Peninsula , situated in the southwest portion of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
The Benson Hills ( 70 ° 28′S 62 ° 17′W ) are a cluster of coastal hills near the head of Smith Inlet in Antarctica , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) east of Berry Massif on the east side of Palmer Land .
Cain Nunatak ( 63 ° 34′S 57 ° 42′W ) is the westernmost of two isolated nunataks on the south side of Broad Valley , situated 3.37 km east - northeast of Kumata Hill on Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica .
Garnerin Point ( 64 ° 41′S 62 ° 10′W ) is a point on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica , projecting into Wilhelmina Bay southeast of Pelseneer Island .
Finback Massif ( 65 ° 41′S 62 ° 25′W ) is a massif in Antarctica , rising to more than 1,000 metres ( 3,300 ft ) between Stubb Glacier and Flask Glacier .
Gavin Ice Piedmont ( 63 ° 44′S 59 ° 0′W ) is an ice piedmont in Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica , about 15 nautical miles ( 30 km ) long and between 3 and 6 nautical miles ( 6 and 11 km ) wide , extending from Charcot Bay to Russell West Glacier .
Mandible Cirque ( 73 ° 7′S 169 ° 15′E ) is a cirque indenting the coast of Daniell Peninsula 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) west - southwest of Cape Phillips , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Karpf Point ( 66 ° 54′S 64 ° 23′W ) is a point along the north side of Mill Inlet , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south of Mount Vartdal , on the east coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Kraut Rocks ( 76 ° 4′S 136 ° 11′W ) are a group of rock outcrops on the snow - covered , lower southwest slopes of the Mount Berlin massif , in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Ford Spur ( 84 ° 51′S 173 ° 50′E ) is a prominent spur which marks the southwestern extremity of Haynes Table , and the confluence of Keltie Glacier and Brandau Glacier in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Toney Mountain is an elongated snow - covered shield volcano , 60 km ( 38 mi ) long and rising to 3,595 m in Richmond Peak , located 56 km ( 35 mi ) SW of Kohler Range in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Russian Gap ( 69 ° 11′S 71 ° 13′W ) is a gap extending in a north - south direction between the Havre Mountains and Rouen Mountains , in the north part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
The Atlantic Club Ridge ( Vrah Atlanticheski Klub \'vr&h a - tlan-'ti - che - ski ' klub\ ) is a ridge rising to 161 m on Hurd Peninsula in Eastern Livingston Island , Antarctica .
Kasumi Rock ( 68 ° 22′S 42 ° 14′E ) is a substantial rock exposure on the coast between Ichime Glacier and Kasumi Glacier in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Geodetic Glacier ( 77 ° 45′S 163 ° 47′E ) is a glacier flowing east from Bettle Peak along the north side of the Thomas Heights into Bowers Piedmont Glacier , on the Scott Coast of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Vund Point ( Bulgarian : нос Вунд , `` Nos Vund '' \'nos ' vund\ ) is the point forming the east extremity of Rugged Island off the west coast of Byers Peninsula of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .

Buell Peninsula ( 70 ° 36′S 164 ° 24′E ) is an ice - covered peninsula terminating in Cape Williams , located between the lower ends of Lillie Glacier , George Glacier and Zykov Glacier , at the northwest end of the Anare Mountains , a major mountain range situated in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Faulkner Nunatak ( 69 ° 36′S 71 ° 42′W ) is a distinctive nunatak , about 200 metres ( 660 ft ) high , just west of Beagle Peak , in the Lassus Mountains , in the northwest part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mount Takahe is a large , snow - covered shield volcano standing 64 km SE of Toney Mountain in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Mount Frödin ( 64 ° 50′S 62 ° 50′W ) is a mountain , about 600 metres ( 2,000 ft ) high , rising 0.5 nautical miles ( 1 km ) east - southeast of Waterboat Point , Paradise Harbor , on Danco Coast , Antarctica .
Panagyurishte Nunatak ( Nunatak Panagyurishte \'nu - na - tak pa - na-'gyu - ri - shte\ ) is a rocky peak of elevation 150 m projecting from Yakoruda Glacier , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .

Mellor Glacier is a tributary glacier , flowing northnortheast between Mount Newton and Mount Maguire and coalescing with Collins Glacier just prior to its junction with Lambert Glacier at Patrick Point , in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
The Caudal Hills ( 73 ° 10′S 161 ° 50′E ) are a group of hills situated within Victoria Land , Antarctica the hills lie between the Sequence Hills and the Lichen Hills on the western margin of upper Rennick Glacier .

Severinghaus Glacier ( 78 ° 40′S 85 ° 15′W ) is a glacier flowing southwestward from Karnare Col along the north side of Mount Strybing and the south side of Mount Craddock into Bender Glacier in southern Sentinel Range , Ellsworth Mountains in Antarctica .
Fur Seal Point , sometimes referred to as Fur Seal Beach , is a cape mid - way along the eastern coast of Clarence Island , the easternmost of the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Rumdoodle Peak , elevation 875 m ASL , is a small but prominent mountain in the north - western part of the North Masson Range in Antarctica , near Mawson Station .
Post Office Hill ( 77 ° 28′S 169 ° 14′E ) is a prominent hill in Antarctica , 430 m , standing 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) northwest of The Knoll and overlooking the Adelie penguin rookery of Cape Crozier , Ross Island .
Laird Glacier ( 84 ° 55′S 169 ° 55′E ) is a tributary glacier , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) long , flowing northeast from the Supporters Range , Antarctica , to enter Keltie Glacier 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) southeast of Ranfurly Point .
