Jannotta Professor of Medieval History and Committee on Social Thought at the University of Chicago , as well as the Dean of the Social Sciences Division at the University and the founding Roman Family Director of the Neubauer Family Collegium for Culture and Society .
W. Russell Neuman is Professor of Media Technology , NYU Steinhardt School of Culture , Education , and Human Development and Professor ( Emeritus ) , Communication Studies , University of Michigan .
Andrew Pollard is an Assistant Director with responsibility for Research Impact at the Institute of Education , University College London , and a Professor of Education at the Graduate School of Education , University of Bristol .
Josef Foschepoth ( born 19 November 1947 ) is a German historian and a professor at the University of Freiburg .
Julia Ching , CM ( Chinese : 秦家懿 ) ( 1934 -- October 26 , 2001 ) was professor of religion , philosophy and East Asian studies at the University of Toronto .
Ruth Chang is a professor of philosophy at Rutgers University .
James Coomarasamy is a British presenter on BBC World Service programme Newshour .
Priscilla K. Coleman , Ph.D. , is a tenured full Professor of Human Development and Family Studies at Bowling Green State University in Ohio .
Jonathan H. Turner ( born September 7 , 1942 ) , is a professor of sociology at University of California , Riverside .
William Veeder ( born September 14 , 1940 ) is a scholar of 19th - century American and British literature and a Professor Emeritus in the Department of English at the University of Chicago .
Henry Seidel Canby ( September 6 , 1878 -- April 5 , 1961 ) was a critic , editor , and Yale University professor .
Edward F. Fischer is a Professor of Anthropology at Vanderbilt University who writes on political economy , development , and culture .
Brad R. Roth is a professor of political science and law at Wayne State University , Detroit .
Edmund Ayrton ( 1734 -- 22 May 1808 ) was an English organist who was Master of the Children of the Chapel Royal .
Dr. Asifa Quraishi is an Assistant Professor of Law at the University of Wisconsin - Madison , where she teaches courses in Islamic law and U.S. constitutional law .
Donald Roden is an associate professor of history at Rutgers University .
Ashley Bouder is an American ballet dancer who is currently a principal dancer at the New York City Ballet .
Elaine Mayes ( born October 1 , 1936 ) is an American photographer and a retired professor at New York University 's Tisch School of the Arts .
Bertell Ollman ( born April 30 , 1935 in Milwaukee ) is a professor of politics at New York University .
David Wojahn ( born 1953 , St. Paul , Minnesota ) is a contemporary American poet who teaches poetry in the Department of English at Virginia Commonwealth University , and in the low residency MFA in Writing program at the Vermont College of Fine Arts .
Virginia Tanner ( April 25 , 1915 -- May 20 , 1979 ) was an American dance instructor and founder of the University of Utah Children 's Dance Theatre .
Tony Tebby is probably most famous for designing Qdos , the computer operating system used in the Sinclair QL personal computer , whilst working as an engineer at Sinclair Research in the early 1980s .
Avraham Heffner ( Hebrew : אברהם הפנר‎ ; 7 May 1935 -- 19 September 2014 ) was an Israeli film and television director , screenwriter , author and Professor Emeritus at the Tel - Aviv University .
George F. Baughman ( 1915 - -2004 ) was the first president of New College of Florida , a vice president of the University of Florida as well as of New York University and treasurer and a rear admiral in the United States Naval Reserve .
Nick Bostrom ( Swedish : Niklas Boström ; born 10 March 1973 ) is a Swedish philosopher at the University of Oxford known for his work on existential risk , the anthropic principle , human enhancement ethics , superintelligence risks , the reversal test , and consequentialism .
Julian Wolpert ( born 1932 ) is Bryant Professor Emeritus of Geography , Public Affairs , and Urban Planning at Princeton University .
Robert S. Galen ( born May 29 , 1946 ) is a physician , Professor Emeritus Epidemiology and former Senior Associate Dean in the College of Public Health at The University of Georgia .
Colin Crouch is currently Emeritus Professor at the University of Warwick .
Claude Sammut is a Professor of Computer Science and Engineering at the University of New South Wales and Head of the Artificial Intelligence Research Group .
Van C. Gessel ( born August 1 , 1950 , Compton , California ) is a former Dean of the BYU College of Humanities at Brigham Young University .
Mary Shanthi Dairiam ( born 17 September 1939 ) is a Malaysian human rights and women 's rights advocate and United Nations ( UN ) official .
Ladislaus Löb ( born 8 May 1933 ) is Professor Emeritus of German at the University of Sussex in England .
Yousef Saad is an I.T. Distinguished Professor of Computer Science in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the University of Minnesota .
Luis Garicano Gabilondo ( Valladolid , 1967 ) is Professor of Economics and Strategy and Head of the Managerial Economics and Strategy Group at the London School of Economics .
Sharon Ashbrook is a Professor of Physical Chemistry at the University of St Andrews .
Anton Amann ( 20 June 1956 -- 6 January 2015 ) was an Austrian chemist and Professor of chemistry at the Innsbruck Medical University .
Bruce Lahn is the William B. Graham professor of Human Genetics at the University of Chicago .
Peter Pershan earned his B.S. at Polytechnic Institute of Brooklyn in 1956 and his Ph.D. in Physics at Harvard University in 1960 for nuclear magnetic resonance under the supervision of Nicolaas Bloembergen .
Larissa Bonfante ( born March 27 , 1931 , in Naples , Italy ) is an Italian - American classicist , Professor of Classics emerita at New York University and an authority on Etruscan language and culture .
Robert G. Frank ( born 1952 ) is the 21st President of the University of New Mexico .
J. Marshall Shepherd is an American meteorologist , professor at the University of Georgia 's Department of Geography , the director of the university 's atmospheric sciences program , and was the president of the American Meteorological Society ( AMS ) in 2013 .
Susan Rose - Ackerman ( born Susan Gould Rose on April 23 , 1942 in Mineola , New York ) is Henry R. Luce Professor of Jurisprudence ( Law and Political Science ) and is co - director of the Center for Law , Economics , and Public Policy at Yale Law School .
Martin van Beynen ( born 1959 ) is a New Zealand writer , print journalist and columnist for the The Press in Christchurch .
Hyman Hurwitz ( 1770 - -1844 ) , was a learned Jew who became first professor of Hebrew at University College , London .
Hessam Nowzari is the Director of the University of Southern California Advanced Periodontics program , since 1995 , and is a Diplomate of the American Board of Periodontology .
George H. Burgess ( born December 25 , 1949 ) is an ichthyologist and fisheries biologist with the Florida Museum of Natural History , University of Florida .
Johanna Gibson is Herchel Smith Professor of Intellectual Property Law in the Centre for Commercial Law Studies , Queen Mary , University of London .
Donald W. Parry Ph.D. is a professor of Hebrew Bible in the Department of Asian and Near Eastern Languages at Brigham Young University .
Ivo Josipović attended the Faculty of Law of the University of Zagreb , from which he graduated passing his bar examination in 1980 .
Alexandre Ricard , born in 1972 , is a French businessman and one of the grandsons of distiller and Pernod Ricard founder , Paul Ricard .
Aubrey Singer CBE ( 21 January 1927 -- 26 May 2007 ) was a British broadcasting executive who spent most of his career at the BBC .
Peter John Wyllie ( b. 8 February 1930 , London , England ) is a British petrologist who was Professor of Geology at the California Institute of Technology from 1983 until his retirement in 1999 .
David Noel Ramírez Padilla ( born January 12 , 1950 ) is the dean of the Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education university system ( ITESM ) which has thirty one campuses in various parts of Mexico .
Sigurd Allern ( born 5 September 1946 ) is a Norwegian media theorist and the first professor of journalism at the University of Oslo .
Philippa Thomas ( born 22 November 1965 ) is a British television Newsreader and journalist , both domestic and foreign , at the BBC and the main presenter of World News Today which airs on BBC World News , BBC News Channel and BBC Four .
Josip Pečarić ( born 3 September 1948 ) is a Croatian Academician , mathematician and the professor of mathematics at the University of Zagreb , Croatia .
Claes Elefalk is a Swedish sports agent at the Creative Artists Agency .
Anne L'Huillier ( born 1958 in Paris ) is a French physicist , and professor of atomic physics at Lund University .
Linda Smircich ( born 1948 ) is a Professor of Management in the Isenberg School of Management , University of Massachusetts Amherst where she teaches Organizational Alternative Paradigms .
Raden Moehamad Djoehana Wiradikarta ( born 18 September 1896 in Bandung , Indonesia -- died in 1986 in Bandung ) was a professor in microbiology and serology at the Bandung Institute of Technology and the faculty of medicine at Padjadjaran University , also in Bandung .
Gerhard Dünnhaupt , FRSC ( born August 15 , 1927 in Bernburg ( Saale ) ) is a German bibliographer , literary historian , emeritus professor of the University of Michigan , an honorary life member of the Modern Language Association of America , and a Life Member of the Academies of Arts , Humanities and Sciences of Canada .
Edward Kamens ( born 19 April 1952 ) is Sumitomo Professor of Japanese Literature at Yale University , where he has taught since 1986 .
Adolph Stöhr ( February 24 , 1855 -- February 10 , 1921 ) was professor of philosophy at the University of Vienna .
Imants Barušs is Professor of Psychology at King 's University College at The University of Western Ontario , Canada .
Janet Fitch is a faculty member in the Master of Professional Writing Program at the University of Southern California , where she teaches fiction .
Tamar Garb is Durning Lawrence Professor in the Department of History of Art at University College London .
Michael Barkun ( born 8 April 1938 ) is professor emeritus of political science at the Maxwell School of Citizenship and Public Affairs , Syracuse University , specializing in political extremism and the relationship between religion and violence .
Kenneth Turan ( /təˈræn/ ; born October 27 , 1946 ) is an American film critic and Lecturer in the Master of Professional Writing Program at the University of Southern California .
John Geanakoplos ( born 1955 ) is an American economist , and the current James Tobin Professor of Economics at Yale University .
Kate Bradbury Griffith aka Kate Griffith ( née Bradbury ) ( 26 August 1854 -- 2 March 1902 ) was a British Egyptologist who assisted in the early development of the Egypt Exploration Society and the Department of Egyptology at University College London ( UCL ) .
Sarah Parker ( born August 23 , 1942 ) is an American judge who served as the Chief Justice of the North Carolina Supreme Court from February 2006 until August 2014 .
Margarita Luti ( also Margherita Luti or La Fornarina , `` the baker 's daughter '' ) was the mistress and model of Raphael .
Thomas R. Kratochwill is the Sears - Bascom Professor of School Psychology at the University of Wisconsin-- Madison , where he directs the School Psychology Program .
Nora Fridrichová ( born 13 September 1977 ) is a Czech television presenter , who works for Czech television channel Česká televize .
Edward F. Wente ( born 1930 ) is an American professor emeritus of Egyptology and the Department of Near Eastern Languages and Civilizations at the University of Chicago .
Rebekka Habermas ( born 3 July 1959 , in Frankfurt am Main ) is a noted German historian , currently professor of modern history at the University of Göttingen , in Germany .
Indira Viswanathan Peterson is a literary critic and the David B. Truman Professor of Asian Studies at Mount Holyoke College .
William Stewart Simkins ( August 25 , 1842 -- February 27 , 1929 ) was a Confederate soldier and professor of law at the University of Texas at Austin .
James Lindgren is a professor of law at Northwestern University .
Megan Henderson ( born February 19 , 1975 ) is a journalist and weekday morning anchor of the 4 am to 7 am KTLA News in Los Angeles .
Helmut Thielicke ( 4 December 1908 in Wuppertal -- 5 March 1986 in Hamburg ) was a German Protestant theologian and rector of the University of Hamburg from 1960 to 1978 .
Gerardo L. Munck ( born October 13 , 1958 ) Argentine by birth , is a professor of international relations for the School of International Relations of the University of Southern California ( USC ) .
James T. Kloppenberg ( born June 23 , 1951 Denver ) is an American historian , and Charles Warren Professor of American History , at Harvard University .
Stuart Flinders ( born December 1960 , Bolton , Lancashire ) is a journalist , reporter and occasional presenter for BBC North West Tonight .
Melanie Sanford ( born June 16 , 1975 ) is an American chemist , who currently works at the University of Michigan , where she holds the positions of Moses Gomberg Collegiate Professor of Chemistry and Arthur F. Thurnau Professor of Chemistry .
William Brantley Aycock ( October 24 , 1915 -- June 20 , 2015 ) was an American educator who served as chancellor of the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill from 1957 until 1964 and was the retired Kenan Professor of Law at the UNC School of Law .
The Oxford Internet Institute was founded in 2001 by Derek Wyatt , then MP for Sittingbourne and Sheppey , and Andrew Graham , Master of Balliol College .
Wikitravel is a web - based collaborative travel guide project , based upon the wiki model , launched by Evan Prodromou and Michele Ann Jenkins in 2003 .
The origin of the Almedalen Week was the speeches made by Olof Palme during several summers in Almedalen .
In 2013 , Amalgamated Dynamics successfully ran a Kickstarter campaign to fund their independent horror film titled Harbinger Down , which is to be directed by Alec Gillis and produced by Tom Woodruff Jr. The film was released in August 2015 features exclusively practical creature effects .
Cooking Vinyl is a UK based independent record company , founded in 1986 by former manager and booking agent Martin Goldschmidt , who remains the current owner and managing director , and distribution manager Pete Lawrence .
Warrior Sports was founded in 1992 by David Morrow , a former lacrosse player .
The Intelligence Summit is an annual conference run principally by John Loftus and funded by an organization he controls , the Intelligence and Homeland Security Educational Center ( IHEC ) ..
Under Nurhaci and his son Hong Taiji , the Aisin Gioro clan of the Jianzhou tribe won hegemony among the rival Jurchen tribes of the northeast , then through warfare and alliances extended its control into Inner Mongolia .
Berkeley Systems was a San Francisco Bay Area software company co - founded in 1987 by Wes Boyd and Joan Blades .
Asia Brewery , Inc. is a Philippines - based diversified beverage company owned by LT Group , Inc. ( PSE : LTG ) , a publicly listed holding company of Lucio Tan .
Co - Founder of Nanosolar Martin Roscheisen stated on his personal blog that nanosolar `` ultimately failed commercially . ''
AOMG is an independent South Korean record label led by Jay Park and Simon D. AOMG is an acronym that stands for the `` Above Ordinary Music Group . ''
Spyglass Entertainment was an American film production company , co - founded by Gary Barber and Roger Birnbaum in 1998 .
Washington H. Soul Pattinson and Company Limited is an Australian investment company founded by businessman Lewy Pattinson .
Sally Fallon Morell is the co - founder and president of The Weston A. Price Foundation .
Mapin Publishing is an Indian art book publishing company started in 1984 by Bipin Shah and Mallika Sarabhai .
La Mandrágora ( Spanish for The Mandrake ) was a Chilean Surrealist group `` officially founded '' on 12 July 1938 by Braulio Arenas ( 1913 - 1988 ) , Teófilo Cid and Enrique Gómez Correa .
Destination Games was an American computer game development company created in April 2000 by Richard Garriott , Robert Garriott and Starr Long , following their departure from Origin Systems .
Little , Brown and Company is an American publisher founded in 1837 by Charles Coffin Little and his partner , James Brown , and for close to two centuries has published fiction and nonfiction by many of America 's finest writers .
Founded in 1930 by George W. Jenkins , Publix is a private corporation that is wholly owned by present and past employees .
Arya Maitreya Mandala is a tantric and Buddhist order founded 1933 by Lama Anagarika Govinda .
Winona Cargile Alexander ( June 21 , 1893 -- October 16 , 1984 ) was a founder of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority , Incorporated at Howard University on January 13 , 1913 .
The Drug Enforcement Administration was established on July 1 , 1973 , by Reorganization Plan No . 2 of 1973 , signed by President Richard Nixon on July 28 .
Logitech International S.A. was co - founded in Apples , Vaud , Switzerland , in 1981 by two Stanford alumni , Daniel Borel and Pierluigi Zappacosta .
Berkeley Earth founder Richard A. Muller told The Guardian `` ... we are bringing the spirit of science back to a subject that has become too argumentative and too contentious , ....
Last Gang Records is a record label that was formed by Canadian music industry lawyer Chris Taylor and concert promoter Donald Tarlton in the Fall of 2003 at the Pop Montreal Music Festival .
Spice Global was established in 1980 by B. K. Modi under the name , Modi Corp. Later , the company came to be known as MCorp Global and Spice Corp , before it finally became Spice Global .
Gächinger Kantorei ( Gächingen Chorale ) is an internationally known German mixed choir , founded by Helmuth Rilling in 1954 in Gächingen ( part of St. Johann close to Reutlingen ) and conducted by him until 2013 , succeeded by Hans - Christoph Rademann .
Cornerstone Barristers was formed in 1880 by Sir Charles Hall as 2 - 3 Gray 's Inn Square .
Clickteam is a software company founded in 1993 by François Lionet , Yves Lamoureux and Francis Poulain and headquartered in Paris , France .
Alexa Internet was founded in April 1996 by American web entrepreneurs Brewster Kahle and Bruce Gilliat .
It was formerly a Soviet design bureau , and was founded by Artem Mikoyan and Mikhail Gurevich as `` Mikoyan and Gurevich '' , with the bureau prefix `` MiG. ''
Helsinki was established as a trading town by King Gustav I of Sweden in 1550 as the town of Helsingfors , which he intended to be a rival to the Hanseatic city of Reval ( today known as Tallinn ) .
Arrêt sur images ( `` Freeze - frame shot '' , also abbreviated as the acronym ASI ) was initially a weekly French television program , created and presented by journalist Daniel Schneidermann and broadcast on La Cinquième from 1995 ( renamed France 5 in January 2002 ) and produced by Carrere group .
Ampex is an American electronics company founded in 1944 by Alexander M. Poniatoff .
Proventus is a privately held Swedish investment company founded in 1980 by Robert Weil .
Asia Times was a newspaper launched in Thailand by Thai tycoon Sondhi Limthongkul in 1995 .
In 2007 , Chris Jones and Aaron Conners founded Big Finish Games , which is staffed primarily by veterans of Access / Indie Built .
Yahoo Boy No Laptop Nation , stylised and popularly known as YBNL Nation , is an independent record label founded by Olamide in 2012 .
Amma Unavagam ( meaning `` Mother Restaurant '' in Tamil ) is a food subsidization program run by the Government of Tamil Nadu in India .
SeaFrance was a ferry company based in France , wholly owned by the French railways , SNCF , which operated ferry services between Calais , France , and Dover , England .
José María Álvarez ( born 31 May 1942 , in Cartagena , Spain ) , is a Spanish poet and novelist .
Jayshree Gadkar ( 21 February 1942 -- 29 August 2008 ) was a noted Marathi and Hindi movie actress and a star of Marathi cinema from the 1950s up to the 1980s .
Abdurrahman Cahit Zarifoğlu ( born 1 July 1940 , Ankara -- d. 7 June 1987 , İstanbul ) , Turkish poet , writer .
Alfred Illingworth ( 25 September 1827 -- 1907 ) , was an English worsted spinner and Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1868 and 1895 .
Veit Stoss ( also : Veit Stoß ; Polish : Wit Stwosz ; before 1450 - about 20 September 1533 ) was a leading German sculptor , mostly in wood , whose career covered the transition between the late Gothic and the Northern Renaissance .
Jean - Jacques Pillot ( 9 August 1808 -- 13 June 1877 ) was a French revolutionary and republican communist .
John William Gerard de Brahm ( 1718 - -c.1799 ) was a German cartographer , engineer and mystic .
Francesco Musotto ( born on 1 February 1947 in Palermo ) is an Italian politician and Member of the European Parliament for the Islands ( elected for the first time in 1999 ) .
Vicenç Badalona Ballestar ( 1929 -- 7 July 2014 ) was a Spanish painter and author .
Mehmet Niyazi Cemali ( Crimean Tatar : ' Memet Niyaziy ' ; January or February 1878 - November 20 , 1931 ) was an Ottoman - born Romanian and Crimean Tatar poet , journalist , schoolteacher , academic , and activist for ethnic Tatar causes .
Deep Dhillon is an Indian film actor who works in Hindi and Punjabi cinema .
Adolphe - Félix Cals ( 17 October 1810 -- 3 October 1880 ) was a French portrait , genre , and landscape painter .
Claude Weisz is a French film director born in Paris .
Klaus Hildebrand ( born 18 November 1941 , Bielefeld , Germany ) is a German liberal - conservative historian whose area of expertise is 19th--20th - century German political and military history .
Gro Dahle ( born 15 May 1962 ) is a Norwegian poet and writer .
Peter , Pieter , or usually Petrus Camper ( 11 May 1722 -- 7 April 1789 ) , was a Dutch physician , anatomist , physiologist , midwife , zoologist , anthropologist , paleontologist and a naturalist .
Jean Marie Joseph Capgras ( 23 August 1873 , Verdun - sur - Garonne -- 27 January 1950 , Paris ) was a French psychiatrist who is best known for the Capgras delusion , a disorder named after him .
Bernat Soria Escoms ( born 7 May 1951 ) is a Spanish politician who served as Minister of Health from 2007 to 2009 .
Leonhard Lapin ( born 29 December 1947 ) is a versatile Estonian artist who has been active in fine art , art theory and architecture as well as in literature .
Vladimir Ćorović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Владимир Ћоровић ; October 27 , 1885 -- April 12 , 1941 ) was a leading 20th - century Serbian historian , member of the Serbian Royal Academy , a future Serbian Academy of Sciences and Arts ( SANU ) .
Mariano Barberán y Tros de Ilarduya ( Guadalajara , Spain , 14 October 1895 - Vicinity of Villahermosa , Mexico , 20 June 1933 ) was a Spanish military aviator .
Lucjan Siemieński ( 1807 - -1877 ) was a Polish Romantic poet , prose writer , and literary critic .
Guido Leo John Christmas Møller , usually known as Christmas Møller ( 3 April 1894 - 13 April 1948 ) was a Danish politician representing the Conservative People 's Party .
Gonzalo Ronquillo de Peñalosa ( died March 10 , 1583 ) , sometimes spelled as Gonçalo Ronquillo Peñaloza was the fourth Spanish governor and captain - general of the Philippines from April 1580 until his death in 1583 .
Rebecca Frayn is an English documentary film maker , screenwriter and novelist .
Józef Pankiewicz ( 29 November 1866 -- 4 July 1940 ) was a Polish painter , graphic artist , and pedagogue .
Charles Foix ( 1 February 1882 - 22 March 1927 ) was a French internist and neurologist .
Marie - Alexandre Alophe ( 1812 - -1883 ) was a French photographer , painter and lithographer .
Fred Terry ( 9 November 1863 -- 17 April 1933 ) was an English actor and theatrical manager .
Charles Lucien Léandre ( 1862 - -1934 ) , French caricaturist and painter , was born at Champsecret ( Orne ) , and studied painting under Émile Bin and Alexandre Cabanel .
Keith Peacock ( born 2 May 1945 in Barnehurst ) is an English former footballer and manager .
Francisco Cascales ( 1564 - -1642 ) was a Spanish erudite , humanist and writer .
Girish Kumar Taurani ( born 30 January 1989 , age 27 ) is an Indian film actor working in the Hindi film industry .
Hugo Ball ( German : ( bal ) ; 22 February 1886 -- 14 September 1927 ) was a German author , poet and one of the leading Dada artists .
Guillermo del Toro Gómez ( Spanish pronunciation : ( ɡiˈʝeɾmo ðel ˈtoɾo ) ; born October 9 , 1964 ) is a Mexican film director , screenwriter , producer , and novelist .
James Raine ( 1791 - -1858 ) was an English antiquarian and topographer .
Michael Sowa ( born 1945 ) is a German artist known mainly for his paintings , which are variously whimsical , surreal , or stunning .
Pierre Chantraine ( French : ( ʃɑ̃tʁɛn ) ; 15 September 1899 -- 30 June 1974 ) was a French linguist .
Cuauhtémoc Cárdenas Solórzano ( Spanish pronunciation : ( kwauˈtemok ˈkarðenas ) ; born May 1 , 1934 ) is a prominent Mexican politician .
Michel Clouscard ( French : ( kluskaʁ ) ; August 6 , 1928 -- February 21 , 2009 ) was a French Marxist philosopher and sociologist .
Silvio Soldini ( Milan , 1958 ) is an Italian film director .
Peter Annet ( 1693 -- 18 January 1769 ) was an English deist and early freethinker .
Indrek Tarand MEP ( born February 3 , 1964 , Tallinn ) is an Estonian politician , reserve officer , civil servant , journalist and historian .
Marujita Díaz ( María del Dulce Nombre Díaz Ruiz ; 27 April 1932 -- 23 June 2015 ) was a Spanish singer and actress .
Sheikh Riza Talabani ( Şêx Rizayê Telebanî in Kurdish ) ( 1835 - -1910 ) , a celebrated Kurdish poet from Kirkuk , Iraq .
Herman Schmalenbach ( November 15 , 1885 -- November 3 , 1950 ) was a German philosopher who refined the concepts of Gemeinschaft and Bund .
Johann Georg Keyßler ( or Keyssler when the letter ß is avoided ; 1693 - -1743 ) was a German polymath , known for his travel writings and his archaeology .
Hans Victor von Unruh ( March 28 , 1806 - February 4 , 1886 ) was a Prussian civil servant and politician , President of the Prussian National Assembly of 1848 and Member of the Reichstag of the German Empire .
Casimir Roumeguère ( 15 August 1828 in Toulouse -- 29 February 1892 in Toulouse ) was a French botanist and mycologist .
Michael McClure was a popular , celebrated professor of English at the California College of Arts and Crafts ( now renamed California College of the Arts ) , in Oakland , California for many years .
Johann Benedict Carpzov II ( 24 April 1639 -- 23 March 1699 ) was a German Christian theologian and Hebraist .
Nicolas de Lamoignon de Basville ( 1648 - -1724 ) was a French intendant over Languedoc in the early 18th century .
Marin Karmitz ( born 7 October 1938 in Bucharest , Romania ) is a French businessman whose career has spanned the French film industry , including director , producer , film distributor , and operator of a chain of cinemas .
Friedrich Wilhelm Ritschl ( 6 April 1806 -- 9 November 1876 ) was a German scholar best known as a student of Plautus .
Monte Melkonian ( classical Armenian : Մոնթէ Մելքոնեան ; reformed : Մոնթե Մելքոնյան ; November 25 , 1957 -- June 12 , 1993 ) was an Armenian left - wing nationalist militant , revolutionary , and commander .
Eliyahu Golomb ( Hebrew : אליהו גולומב‎ , 2 March 1893 -- 11 June 1945 ) was the leader of the Jewish defense effort in Mandate Palestine and chief architect of the Haganah , the underground military organization for defense of the Yishuv between 1920 and 1948 .
Sandro Continenza ( 13 July 1920 -- 21 November 1996 ) was an Italian screenwriter .
Hartwig Fischer ( born 14 December 1962 ) is a German art historian and museum director .
Bernard Le Nail ( February 1946 -- 5 January 2010 ) was a French writer and Breton militant .
Elisabetta Gardini ( born 3 June 1956 ) is an Italian actress and politician from Veneto .
Sigmund Theophil Staden ( 6 November 1607 -- 30 July 1655 ) was an important early German composer .
Sir William Temple , 1st Baronet ( 25 April 1628 -- 27 January 1699 ) was an English statesman and essayist .
Moishe Oysher ( Yiddish : משה אוישר , ( born 1906 in Lipkon ( Lipcani ) , Bessarabia , Imperial Russia -- died 27 November 1958 , New Rochelle , New York ) was a Romanian cantor and Yiddish theatre actor . He is considered one of the most entertaining chazanim ( cantors ) ever recorded .
Robert Shirley , Viscount Tamworth ( 28 December 1692 -- 5 July 1714 ) was an English nobleman and politician .
Konrad Haenisch ( 13 March 1876 - 28 April 1925 ) was a German Social Democratic Party politician and part of `` the radical Marxist Left '' of German politics .
Olaf Glaeseker ( born 1961 in Oldenburg ) is a German political consultant , journalist , publicist , and a close confidant of former President Christian Wulff .
Lluís Homar i Toboso ( born April 20 , 1957 ) is a Spanish actor and theater director from Barcelona .
Furio Scarpelli ( 16 December 1919 -- 28 April 2010 ) , also called Scarpelli , was an Italian screenwriter , famous for his collaboration on numerous Commedia all'italiana films with Agenore Incrocci , forming the duo Age & Scarpelli .
Rudolf Arnheim ( July 15 , 1904 -- June 9 , 2007 ) was a German - born author , art and film theorist , and perceptual psychologist .
Tang Haoming ( Chinese : 唐浩明 ; pinyin : Táng Hàomíng ; born October 1946 ) , born as Deng Yunsheng ( simplified Chinese : 邓云生 ; traditional Chinese : 鄧雲生 ; pinyin : Dèng Yúnshēng ) , is a Chinese novelist .
Suzanne Duchamp - Crotti ( 20 October 1889 -- 11 September 1963 ) was a French Dadaist painter .
Inger Christensen ( 16 January 1935 -- 2 January 2009 ) was a Danish poet , novelist , essayist and editor considered the foremost Danish poetic experimentalist of her generation .
Niels Kaj Jerne , FRS ( December 23 , 1911 -- October 7 , 1994 ) was a Danish immunologist .
Tadeusz Stefan Zieliński ( Russian : Фадде́й Фра́нцевич Зели́нский ; near Uman , Kiev Governorate , Russian Empire , September 14 , 1859 -- May 8 , 1944 , Schondorf , Upper Bavaria ) was a prominent Polish classical philologist , historian , translator of Sophocles , Euripides and other classical authors into Russian .
Kinga Göncz ( born 8 November 1947 ) is a Hungarian academic and the former Minister of Foreign Affairs of Hungary between 2006 and 2009 .
Georges Marion ( 1 June 1869 , in Fixin , Côte - d'Or -- 17 October 1960 , in Paris ) was a French surgeon and urologist .
Gustav Seyffarth ( 13 July 1796 -- 17 November 1885 ) was a German - American Egyptologist , born in Uebigau .
Karim Alrawi ( Arabic كريم الراوي ) is a writer born in Alexandria , Egypt .
Norbert Bolz ( born April 17 , 1953 ) is a German philosopher and media theorist .
Lucie Šafářová (; born 4 February 1987 ) is a professional Czech tennis player from Brno .
Arnold van Gennep , in full Charles - Arnold Kurr van Gennep ( 23 April 1873 -- 7 May 1957 ) was a noted Dutch - German - French ethnographer and folklorist .
Carlos García Cantarero ( born November 4 , 1961 ) is a Spanish footballer and manager .
Maurice Benayoun ( aka MoBen or 莫奔 ) ( born 29 March 1957 in Mascara , Algeria ) is a French pioneer new - media artist and theorist based in Paris and Hong Kong .
Reinhold F. Glei ( German : ( glaɪ ) ; born 11 Juni , 1959 in Remscheid ) is a German philologist and translator .
Germain Habert de Cérisy ( 1615 -- May 1654 ) was a French churchman and poet .
Miguel Cabrera Cabrera ( born 1948 , Gran Canaria , Spain ) is a Spanish architect and politician whose sphere of political action has been the Canary Island of Fuerteventura .
Luis Cid Pérez , known as Carriega ( born 9 December 1929 ) is a Spanish former professional football coach who managed a number of club sides including Sporting de Gijón , Real Zaragoza , Sevilla , Real Betis , Atlético Madrid and UE Figueres .
Geminiano Montanari ( June 1 , 1633 -- October 13 , 1687 ) was an Italian astronomer , lens - maker , and proponent of the experimental approach to science .
František Kupka ( September 23 , 1871 -- June 24 , 1957 ) , also known as Frank Kupka or François Kupka , was a Czech painter and graphic artist .

Stéphane Venne ( born July 2 , 1941 in Verdun , Quebec , Canada ) is a French - Canadian songwriter and composer .

Francisco de Ulloa ( pronounced : ( fɾanˈθisko de uˈʎoa ) ) ( died 1540 ) was a Spanish explorer who explored the west coast of present - day Mexico under the commission of Hernán Cortés .

Lord William George Frederick Cavendish - Scott - Bentinck ( 27 February 1802 -- 21 September 1848 ) , better known as Lord George Bentinck , was an English Conservative politician and racehorse owner , noted for his role ( with Benjamin Disraeli ) in unseating Sir Robert Peel over the Corn Laws .
Rodolfo Martín Villa ( born 3 October 1934 ) is a Spanish engineer and politician , who served in various capacities in cabinets of the Spanish transition to democracy , including interior minister and first deputy prime minister .
Alessandro Ferrara ( born 1953 in Trieste ) is an Italian philosopher , currently Professor of Political Philosophy at the University of Rome Tor Vergata and former President of the Italian Association for Political Philosophy .
Wolfgang Behringer is a German historian specialising in the witchcraft beliefs of Early Modern Europe .
Walter Charleton ( 2 February 1619 -- 24 April 1707 ) was a natural philosopher , an English writer .
Richard Texier is a French painter and sculptor .
Aurélien Barrau ( 19 May 1973 in Neuilly - sur - Seine ) is a French physicist and philosopher , specialized in astroparticle physics , black holes and cosmology .
Zef Jubani ( 1818 - -1880 ) born Zef Ndokillia was an Albanian folklorist , philosopher and activist of the Albanian National Awakening .
Cristóbal Valero ( died December 1789 ) was a Spanish painter .
Claudine Doury ( born 1959 in Blois ) is a French photographer living in Paris .
Tadeusz Jan Kowalski ( 1889 - 1948 ) was a Polish orientalist , expert on Middle East Muslim culture and languages .
Tale Ognenovski ( Macedonian : Тале Огненовски ) ( April 27 , 1922 - June 19 , 2012 ) was a Macedonian multi - instrumentalist : clarinet , reed pipe ( instrument ) ( recorder ) , tin whistle , small bagpipe , zourla ( zurla ) and drum , composer and bandleader .
Philippe Chéry ( 1759 -- 1838 ) , a French historical and portrait painter , was a pupil of Vien .

Kenji Uematsu ( born 28 October 1976 in Portugalete , Vizcaya ) is a Spanish judoka . His father is Japanese and his mother is Spanish .

Maxwell Ruthven Thornton ( 11 July 1878 -- 30 August 1950 ) was an English Liberal politician and lawyer .
Menahem Stern ( Hebrew : מנחם שטרן‎ ; March 5 , 1925 -- June 22 , 1989 ) was an internationally acclaimed Israeli historian of the Second Temple period .
Otto Freundlich ( 10 July 1878 -- 9 March 1943 ) was a German painter and sculptor of Jewish origin and one of the first generation of abstract artists .
Sir Frank Fraser Darling FRSE LLD ( born Frank Darling , 23 June 1903 -- 22 October 1979 ) was an English ecologist , ornithologist , farmer , conservationist and author , who is strongly associated with the highlands and islands of Scotland .
Émile Roubaud ( March 2 , 1882 in Paris -- September 30 , 1962 in Paris ) was a French biologist and entomologist known for his work on paludism , yellow fever and sleeping sickness .
Vittoria Aganoor ( Armenian : Վիկտորիա Աղանուր , 26 May 1855 -- 9 April 1910 ) was an Italian poet with Armenian ancestry .

Annibale Carracci ( Italian pronunciation : ( anˈnibale karˈrattʃi ) ; November 3 , 1560 -- July 15 , 1609 ) was an Italian Baroque painter .
Irene Pivetti ( born 4 April 1963 ) is an Italian journalist and politician , she was President of the Italian Chamber of Deputies from 1994 to 1996 .
Willi Baumeister ( 22 January 1889 -- 31 August 1955 ) was a German painter , scenic designer , art professor , and typographer .
Manuel Bretón de los Herreros ( December 19 , 1796 , Quel ( Logrono ) -- November 8 , 1873 , Madrid ) was a Spanish dramatist , educated at Madrid .

Gurbachan Singh Bhullar ( born March 18 , 1937 ) is a Punjabi author of short stories .

Henry Aldrich ( 1647 -- 14 December 1710 ) was an English theologian and philosopher .

José Luis Garci ( born as José Luis García Muñoz ; 20 January 1944 ) is a Spanish director , producer , critic , TV presenter , screenwriter and author .
Pedro José Amadeo Pissis Marín ( Brioude , France , May 17 , 1812 -- January 21 , 1889 , Santiago de Chile ) was a French geologist who served the Chilean government in the 19th century .
Juan Hormaechea Cazón ( born 5 June 1939 ) is a former Spanish politician and former President of Cantabria between 1987 and 1990 , and again from 1991 to 1995 .
Mahesh Bhatt ( born 20 September 1948 ) is an Indian film director , producer and screenwriter known for his works exclusively in Hindi cinema .
Claudio Lolli ( Bologna , March 28 , 1950 ) is an Italian singer - songwriter , poet , writer and secondary school teacher .
Boileau - Narcejac is the nom de plume by which French crime fiction writers Pierre Boileau ( 28 April 1906 -- 16 January 1989 ) and Pierre Ayraud , aka Thomas Narcejac ( 3 July 1908 -- 9 June 1998 ) collaborated .
François Bonnemer was a French painter and engraver who was born at Falaise in 1637 .
Augustin Roux ( French : ( ʁu ) ; 26 January 1726 -- 28 June 1776 ) was a French doctor , encyclopedist and man of letters during the Age of Enlightenment .
Kaikala Satyanarayana is an Indian film actor , producer and director in Telugu Cinema .
Ernest Wichner ( born in Zăbrani , 17 April 1952 ) is a German writer , editor and literary translator .
Arrigo Petacco ( Castelnuovo Magra , 1929 ) is an Italian writer , historian and journalist .
Nicole El Karoui is a French - Tunisian mathematician , and pioneer in the development of mathematical finance , born May 29 , 1944 , in Paris ( maiden name `` Nicole Schvartz '' ) .
Hilton Edwards ( 2 February 1903 -- 18 November 1982 ) was an English - born Irish actor , lighting designer and theatrical producer .
Keith Richards ( born 18 December 1943 ) is an English musician , singer , songwriter , actor , and one of the original members of the rock band The Rolling Stones .
Jean - François - Auguste Le Dentu ( 21 June 1841 in Basse - Terre ( Guadeloupe ) -- 26 October 1926 in Paris ) was a French surgeon .
William Auld ( 6 November 1924 -- 11 September 2006 ) was a Scottish poet , author , translator and magazine editor who wrote chiefly in Esperanto .
Dan Rhodes ( born 1972 ) is an English writer , possibly best known for the novel Timoleon Vieta Come Home ( 2003 ) , a subversion of the popular Lassie Come Home movie .

Cristóbal Colón de Carvajal y Gorosábel , 18th Duke of Veragua , ( October 4 , 1949 - ) is a Spanish nobleman , businessman and formerly an officer , helicopter pilot , and commander of a naval vessel in the Spanish Navy .
Israel Gohberg ( Hebrew : ישראל גוכברג‎ ; Russian : Изра́иль Цу́дикович Го́хберг ; 23 August 1928 -- 12 October 2009 ) was a Bessarabian - born Soviet and Israeli mathematician , most known for his work in operator theory and functional analysis , in particular linear operators and integral equations .
William Bullokar was a 16th - century printer who devised a 40-letter phonetic alphabet for the English language .
Miguel Ángel Lotina Oruechebarría ( born 18 June 1957 ) is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a striker , and a current manager .

Jane Barker ( 1652 - 1732 ) was a popular English fiction writer , poet , and a staunch Jacobite .

Manuel Martí ( 1663 - -1737 ) was a Spanish archeologist , humanist , writer , and hellenist .

Jean - Jacques Burlamaqui ( French : ( byʁlamaki ) ; 24 June 1694 -- 3 April 1748 ) was a Swiss legal and political theorist who popularised a number of ideas propounded by other thinkers .
Iraj Afshar ( 8 October 1925 -- 9 March 2011 ) ( Persian : ایرج افشار‎‎ ) was a bibliographer , historian , and an iconic figure in the field of Persian studies .

Marion Montaigne ( born April 8 , 1980 ) is a French cartoonist , known particularly for her popular science comics .

Guido Boggiani ( 1861 - -1902 ) was an Italian painter , draftsman , photographer , and ethnologist who in 1887 traveled through the interior of Brazil , Bolivia and Paraguay to document the lives of Indians in the region .

Lorenzo Acquarone ( born 25 February 1931 in Ventimiglia ) is an Italian lawyer and politician .
Émile Peynaud ( June 29 , 1912 -- July 18 , 2004 ) was a French oenologist and researcher who has been credited with revolutionizing winemaking in the latter half of the 20th century , and has been called `` the forefather of modern oenology '' .

Rodrigo de Quiroga López de Ulloa ( c. 1512 -- February 20 , 1580 ) was a Spanish conquistador of Galician origin .

Nicholas Camusat was a French historian who was born at Troyes in 1575 , and died in 1655 .
William of Tyre ( Latin : Willelmus Tyrensis ; c. 1130 -- 29 September 1186 ) was a medieval prelate and chronicler .

Beverly Fawell ( September 17 , 1930 -- June 22 , 2013 ) was an Illinois politician from Glen Ellyn , part of a family prominent in the Republican Party in Du Page County , Illinois ( her brother - in - law was Congressman Harris Fawell ) .
Tom Burpee ( born 1885 or 1886 ) was elected the first leader of the Communist Party of Canada in May 1921 .
Bijendra Singh ( born 25 December 1956 ) is an Indian politician . He stood for the 2004 Lok Sabha elections on the Indian National Congress ticket and had been a Member of Parliament from Aligarh .
Jayashree Banerjee ( 1938- ) is a leader of Bharatiya Janata Party from Madhya Pradesh .
Sanjeev Balyan is a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party and has won the Indian general elections , 2014 from the Muzaffarnagar ( Lok Sabha constituency ) .

Jenny Mikakos ( born 25 January 1969 ) is an Australian politician for the Australian Labor Party .
Ketil Solvik - Olsen ( born 14 February 1972 ) is a Norwegian politician who has been Minister of Transport and Communications in the Solberg cabinet and second deputy leader of the Progress Party since 2013 .
Alfonso Durazo Montaño ( born 11 July 1954 ) is a Mexican politician and was member of the Institutional Revolutionary Party ( PRI ) who served as chief spokesman and private secretary of President Vicente Fox .
Thomas J. Lynch , Jr. was an American Democratic Party politician from Middletown Township , New Jersey , who served on the Monmouth County , New Jersey Board of Chosen Freeholders .
Peggy Farrell ( 15 November 1920 -- 17 January 2003 ) was an Irish businesswoman who came to prominence through the Irish Countrywomen 's Association and had a brief career as a Fianna Fáil politician in Ireland .
Tom Parlon ( born 19 August 1953 ) is a former Irish Progressive Democrats politician .
Ivan Black ( 6 July 1913 -- 8 July 1990 ) was an Australian politician and a member of the Liberal Party .
Pt . Shri Ram Nagina Mishra is a former member of Lok Sabha and a leader of Bharatiya Janata Party .
Line Henriette Holten Hjemdal ( born 18 October 1971 in Sarpsborg ) is a Norwegian politician for the Christian Democratic Party and 5th Vice President of the Storting .
Jon M. Davis is a United States Marine Corps Lieutenant General currently serving as the Deputy Commandant for Aviation .

The King 's Division is a British Army command , training and administrative apparatus designated for infantry regiments in the North of England .

The 3rd Battalion , Parachute Regiment ( 3 PARA ) , is a battalion sized formation of the British Army 's Parachute Regiment and is a subordinate unit within 16 Air Assault Brigade .

The Northern Fleet ( Russian : Северный флот , Severnyy Flot ; named Red Banner Northern Fleet in Soviet time ) is a unit of the Russian Navy responsible for the defense of northwestern Russia .

Hans - Joachim Marseille ( 13 December 1919 -- 30 September 1942 ; German pronunciation : ( hants joˈaχɪm mɑrˈseɪ ) ) was a Luftwaffe fighter pilot and flying ace during World War II . He is noted for his aerial battles during the North African Campaign and his Bohemian lifestyle .

The Worcestershire Regiment was a line infantry regiment of the line in the British Army , formed in 1881 under the Childers Reforms by the amalgamation of the 29th ( Worcestershire ) Regiment of Foot and the 36th ( Herefordshire ) Regiment of Foot .
Captain George Miller Bligh ( 1780 - -1834 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy , who saw service during the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars , eventually rising to the rank of Captain .
The 142nd ( 6th London ) Brigade ( 142 Bde ) was an infantry brigade of the Territorial Army , part of the British Army , that served in World War I and in World War II remained in the United Kingdom throughout the war .
Major General Thomas Staunton St Clair , KH ( 1785 -- 1846 ) was a British Army officer known for his water - colour paintings which recorded British colonies in Gibraltar .
Francis Mallory was born in Elizabeth City County , Virginia , attended Hampton Academy and was appointed midshipman in the United States Navy where he served in 1822 - -1828 .
Elisha Hunt Rhodes ( March 21 , 1842 -- January 14 , 1917 ) was an American soldier who served in the Union Army of the Potomac for the entire duration of the American Civil War , rising from corporal to colonel of his regiment by war 's end .
The 29th ( Worcestershire ) Regiment of Foot was , from 1694 to 1881 , an infantry regiment of the British Army .
Kathlene Contres ( born July 13 , 1955 ) , is a former United States Navy captain who was the ranking female Hispanic American line officer on active duty .
Frank Sweigart is a former officer in the United States Navy .
Admiral Sir Henry Harvey , KB ( July 1743 -- 28 December 1810 ) was a long - serving officer of the British Royal Navy during the second half of the eighteenth century .

Richard Lestock ( 22 February 1679 -- 17 December 1746 ) was an officer in the Royal Navy , eventually rising to the rank of Admiral .

The 157th ( Highland Light Infantry ) Brigade was an infantry brigade of the British Army .
General Sir Henry Frederick Campbell , KCB , GCH ( 10 July 1769 -- 3 September 1856 ) was a soldier of the British Army .

Mark P. Fitzgerald ( born 1951 ) is a retired United States Navy admiral .

A Leyden jar , or Leiden jar , is a device that `` stores '' static electricity between two electrodes on the inside and outside of a glass jar .
In topology , a branch of mathematics , Borel 's theorem , due to Armand Borel , says the cohomology ring of a classifying space or a classifying stack is a polynomial ring .

The Milgram experiment on obedience to authority figures was a series of social psychology experiments conducted by Yale University psychologist Stanley Milgram .
The Tversky index , named after Amos Tversky , is an asymmetric similarity measure on sets that compares a variant to a prototype .
Chancery Lane takes its name from the historic High Court of Chancery , which started its association with the area when Robert de Chesney , the Bishop of Lincoln acquired the ' old Temple ' in 1161 .
Berborite is a beryllium borate mineral with the chemical formula Be2(BO3)(OH , F )
The Place d'Italie takes its name from its proximity to the Avenue d'Italie , which , traditionally , has been the point of departure on the road that links Paris and Italy , a route now called the RN7 ( Route nationale 7 ) .
The Gould transcontinental system was a system of railroads assembled by George Jay Gould I and the Fuller Syndicate in the early 1900s .
Pelagosite is a form of pisolitic aragonite ( CaCO3 ) whose type locality is the Croatian island group of Palagruža ( Italian Pelagosa , whence the name ) in the middle of the Adriatic .
The Prix Dentan is a Swiss literary award , specifically of the canton of Vaud , created in 1984 and named for Professor Michel Dentan .
Freivalds ' algorithm ( named after Rūsiņš Mārtiņš Freivalds ) is a probabilistic randomized algorithm used to verify matrix multiplication .
Quartier Concordia is a neighbourhood redevelopment project centred on Concordia University 's Sir George Williams campus in downtown Montreal , Quebec , Canada .
Heraklion International Airport , `` Nikos Kazantzakis '' ( IATA : HER , ICAO : LGIR ) is the primary airport on the island of Crete , Greece , and the country 's second busiest airport after Athens International Airport .
51826 Kalpanachawla ( 2001 OB34 ) is an asteroid named for Indian - born astronaut Kalpana Chawla , who was killed in the STS-107 ( Columbia ) space shuttle reentry disaster on February 1 , 2003 .
The Kapp Putsch , also known as the Kapp - Lüttwitz Putsch after its leaders Wolfgang Kapp and Walther von Lüttwitz , was an attempted coup on 13 March 1920 which aimed to undo the German Revolution of 1918 - -1919 , overthrow the Weimar Republic and establish a right - wing autocratic government in its place .
In mathematical logic , Goodstein 's theorem is a statement about the natural numbers , proved by Reuben Goodstein in 1944 , which states that every Goodstein sequence eventually terminates at 0 .
The Leo - Baeck - Medal has been awarded since 1978 by the Leo Baeck Institute of New York and is given for special efforts in German - Jewish reconciliation .
In number theory , the Erdős arcsine law , named after Paul Erdős , states that the prime divisors of a number have a distribution related to the arcsine distribution .
Barnaul Airport is named after Soviet cosmonaut Gherman Titov , an Altai Krai native who was the second human being ( after Yuri Gagarin ) to visit outer space .
Neumayer - Station III , also known as Neumayer III after geophysicist Georg von Neumayer , is a German Antarctic research station of the Alfred - Wegener - Institut .
The Foucault pendulum ( English pronunciation : /fuːˈkoʊ/ foo - KOH ; French pronunciation : ​(fuˈko ) ) , or Foucault 's pendulum , named after the French physicist Léon Foucault , is a simple device conceived as an experiment to demonstrate the rotation of the Earth .
The Pierre Laporte Bridge ( French : Pont Pierre - Laporte ) is the longest main span suspension bridge in Canada .
D'Holbach 's Coterie ( la coterie holbachique was the phrase coined by Jean - Jacques Rousseau ) was a group of radical French Enlightenment thinkers who met regularly at the salon of the atheist philosophe Baron d'Holbach in the years approximately 1750 - -1780 .

Nicotine is named after the tobacco plant Nicotiana tabacum , which in turn is named after the French ambassador in Portugal , Jean Nicot de Villemain , who sent tobacco and seeds to Paris in 1560 , presented to the French King , and who promoted their medicinal use .
USS Puffer ( SSN-652 ) , a Sturgeon - class attack submarine , was the second ship of the United States Navy to be named for the pufferfish , a fish which inflates its body with air .
The Order of Nakhimov ( Russian : `` Орден Нахимова '' ) is a military decoration of the Russian Federation named in honour of Russian admiral Pavel Nakhimov ( 1802 - 1855 ) and bestowed to naval officers for outstanding military leadership .
The name Coevorden means `` cow ford(s ) '' or `` cow crossing '' , similar to Bosporus or Oxford .
Causa Guttenberg refers to the German political affair that led to the resignation of Karl - Theodor zu Guttenberg as Minister of Defence of Germany on 1 March 2011 .
In geometry , a Wythoff construction , named after mathematician Willem Abraham Wythoff , is a method for constructing a uniform polyhedron or plane tiling .
In mathematics , the Crofton formula , named after Morgan Crofton ( 1826 - -1915 ) , is a classic result of integral geometry relating the length of a curve to the expected number of times a `` random '' line intersects it .
The Levi - Civita connection is named after Tullio Levi - Civita , although originally `` discovered '' by Elwin Bruno Christoffel .
USS America ( LHA-6 ) , the fourth American warship to be named for the United States of America , is the first of the America - class amphibious assault ships for the U.S. Navy .
The Barlow lens , named after Peter Barlow , is a diverging lens which , used in series with other optics in an optical system , increases the effective focal length of an optical system as perceived by all components that are after it in the system .
Sufnersee is a reservoir between Splügen and Sufers on the Hinterrhein river in the Grisons , Switzerland .
The Dithmarscher Eiderwatt , officially the Dithmarscher Eidervorland mit Watt ( `` Dittmarschen Eider Foreland and Watt '' ) , is a nature reserve in the districts of Dithmarschen and Nordfriesland in the north German state of Schleswig - Holstein .

The Bezold effect is an optical illusion , named after a German professor of meteorology , Wilhelm von Bezold ( 1837 - -1907 ) , who discovered that a color may appear different depending on its relation to adjacent colors .

Charles Boit ( Stockholm , 10 August 1662 -- Paris , 6 February 1727 ) was a Swedish painter in vitreous enamels who mostly worked in England , Austria and France .

Andreas Sigismund Marggraf ( German : ( ˈmaʀkɡʀaːf ) ; 3 March 1709 -- 7 August 1782 ) was a German chemist from Berlin , then capital of the Margraviate of Brandenburg , and a pioneer of analytical chemistry .
Johann Jakob Wepfer ( December 23 , 1620 -- January 26 , 1695 ) was a Swiss pathologist and pharmacologist who was a native of Schaffhausen .
Frederick Van Voorhies Holman ( August 29 , 1852 -- July 6 , 1927 ) was a prominent lawyer and civic leader of the late 19th and early 20th centuries in Portland in the U.S. state of Oregon .
Raoul Caudron born December 7 , 1883 in Paris - died June 1 , 1958 in Saint Étienne ) was a French football Coach In 1930 Caudron coached France in the first FIFA World Cup .
Bruno Kaiser ( born and died Berlin : 5 February 1911 - 27 January 1982 ) was a Marxist scholar of German studies who became a journalist and , during the Nazi period , a resistance activist .
Jurij Slatkonja ( German : Georg von Slatkonia , also Jurij Chrysippus ; 21 March 1456 - -26 April 1522 ) was a Carniolan choirmaster and the first residential Bishop of Vienna .
Henk Bruna ( born 11 June 1916 in Utrecht , died 22 February 2008 in Huis ter Heide ) was a Dutch publisher and director of the stationery and bookstore chain Bruna .

Demetrio Castillo Duany was born in Santiago de Cuba , into one of the leading families of the eastern region of Cuba and he went to France for his education .
Paul Poiret ( 20 April 1879 , Paris , France -- 30 April 1944 , Paris ) was a leading French fashion designer during the first two decades of the 20th century .
Mario Coppola ( Rome , February 5 , 1937 - Rome , March 5 , 2011 ) was an Italian physicist active in the field of nuclear physics .
Emidio Taliani was born in Montegallo , and studied at the University of Rome , from where he obtained his doctorates in theology and in canon and civil law .
Imre Hódos ( January 10 , 1928 in Hajdúnánás - April 23 , 1989 in Debrecen ) was a Hungarian wrestler and Olympic champion in Greco - Roman wrestling .
Salamon Berger ( 25 February 1858 -- 11 January 1934 ) was a Croatian Jewish industrialist , textile trader , and founder and first director of the Ethnographic Museum in Zagreb .
Junior Wells ( December 9 , 1934 -- January 15 , 1998 ) , born Amos Wells Blakemore Jr. , was an American Chicago blues vocalist , harmonica player , and recording artist .
István Örkény ( 5 April 1912 , Budapest -- 24 June 1979 , Budapest ) was a Hungarian writer whose plays and novels often featured grotesque situations .
Artúr Harmat ( Bojná , 27 June 1885 - Budapest , 26 April 1962 ) was a Hungarian composer .

Camillo Olivetti ( August 1868 in Ivrea , Piedmont , Italy -- December 1943 in Biella , Italy ) was an Italian electrical engineer and founder of Olivetti & Co. , SpA. , the Italian manufacturer of computers , printers and other business machines .
Bernard Jarre ( or Garves ) ( died 1328 ) was a French Cardinal in the period of the Avignon papacy .
Vittorio Benussi ( January 17 , 1878 in Trieste -- November 24 , 1927 in Padua ) was an Italian psychologist .

Marco Ajmone - Marsan ( 1859 -- Turin , 1918 ) was an Italian businessman .
Damayanthi ( 1927 -- 20 November 2010 ) , better known by her stage name Kozhikode Santha Devi , was an Indian Malayalam film and stage actress .

Pietro Raimondi ( December 20 , 1786 , Rome -- October 30 , 1853 ) was an Italian composer , transitional between the Classical and Romantic eras .
Domingo Elizondo ( c. 1710 - died 1 June 1783 , Madrid ) was a Spanish soldier from Navarre who lived in the late 18th century .
François - Xavier Octavie Fontaine ( 7 November 1762 in Saint - Remy , Haute - Saône - 17 May 1812 in Paris ) served in the French military in the American War of Independence , the French Revolutionary Wars , and the Napoleonic Wars .

Victor Gruen was born on July 18 , 1903 , in a middle - class Jewish family in Vienna , Austria .
Professor William Thelwall Thomas MBE , ChM , FRCS ( 1865 - -1927 ) was a Welsh surgeon who worked in Liverpool .

Max Rothmann ( April 26 , 1868 - August 12 , 1915 ) was a German neuroanatomist and physiologist who was a native of Berlin .
Carl Anton von Meyer ( in Russian : Карл Анто́нович фон Ме́йер , Karl Antonovich von Meyer ) ( 1 April 1795 in Vitebsk - 24 February 1855 in Saint Petersburg ) was a German , Russified botanist and explorer .

Thomas Birch Freeman ( 9 December 1809 in Twyford , Hampshire -- 10 August 1890 in Accra ) was a Methodist missionary and colonial official in West Africa .
Georg Franz Hoffmann was a German botanist and lichenologist , who was born January 13 , 1760 in Marktbreit , Germany , and died March 17 , 1826 in Moscow , Russia .
Jean de La Grange ( a.k.a . Jean de Lagrange ) ( c.1325 -- April 25 , 1402 ) was a French prelate and politician , active during the reigns of Charles V and Charles VI , and an important member of the papal curia at Avignon , at the time of the Western Schism .
Vishnu Ganesh Pingle was an Indian revolutionary and a member of the Ghadar Party who was one of those executed in 1915 following the Lahore conspiracy trial for his role in the Ghadar conspiracy .
Pedro Salinas y Serrano ( 27 November 1891 , Madrid -- 4 December 1951 , Boston ) was a Spanish poet , a member of the Generation of ' 27 , as well as a university teacher , scholar and literary critic .
Nicolae Rădescu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( nikoˈla.e rəˈdesku ) ; 30 March 1874 , Călimănești -- 16 May 1953 , New York City ) was a Romanian army officer and political figure .
Harald Leipnitz ( 22 April 1926 -- 21 November 2000 ) was a German actor , who was born in Wuppertal and died in Munich .
Erwin von Steinbach ( c. 1244 -- 17 January 1318 ) was a German architect , and was a central figure in the construction of the Strasbourg Cathedral .
Imre König ( Koenig ) aka Mirko Kenig ( Sept 2 , 1901 , Gyula , Hungary -- 1992 , Santa Monica , California ) was a Hungarian chess master .
Augustus Matthiessen , FRS ( 2 January 1831 , London -- 6 October 1870 , London ) , the son of a merchant , was a British chemist and physicist who obtained his PhD in Germany at the University of Gießen in 1852 with Johann Heinrich Buff .
Herbert Hall Turner FRS ( 13 August 1861 , Leeds -- 20 August 1930 , Stockholm ) was a British astronomer and seismologist .
Joseph Désiré Tholozan was a Franco - Mauritians physician born on October 9 , 1820 in Diego Garcia ( Mauritius ) and died on July 30 , 1897 in Tehran ( Iran ) .
Eberhard Gothein ( 29 October 1853 in Neumarkt -- 13 November 1923 in Berlin ) was a German Economist and Historian .
Anthony Benezet , born Antoine Bénézet ( January 31 , 1713 -- May 3 , 1784 ) , was a French - born American abolitionist and educator who was active in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Carlo Poerio ( 1803-April 28 , Naples - 1867 , Florence ) was an Italian poet , Risorgimento and 1848 Revolution activist , politician , and brother of Alessandro Poerio .

Aloys Lütolf ( born 23 July 1824 , in Gettnau near Willisau , Switzerland ; died at Lucerne , 8 April 1879 ) was a Swiss Catholic ecclesiastical historian .

Aimé - Jules Dalou ( 31 December 1838 , in Paris -- 15 April 1902 , in Paris ) was a French sculptor , recognized as one of the most brilliant virtuosos of nineteenth - century France , admired for his perceptiveness , execution , and unpretentious realism .
Wilhelm Michaelsen ( born 9 October 1860 in Hamburg , Germany , died 18 February 1937 ) was a German zoologist .
Leopold Gratz ( November 4 , 1929 , Vienna -- March 2 , 2006 , Vienna ) was an Austrian politician .

Renée Aspe ( 3 October 1922 -- 17 September 1969 ) was a French artist who lived and worked in Toulouse and Sète .

Austen Kark died at the age of 75 in the Potters Bar rail crash , in which his wife was severely injured .
Mary Linwood ( 1755 - -1845 ) was a needle woman who exhibited her worsted embroidery or crewel embroidery in Leicester and London , and was the school mistress of a private school later known as Mary Linwood Comprehensive School .
François Auguste Victor Grignard ( May 6 , 1871 in Cherbourg - December 13 , 1935 in Lyon ) was a Nobel Prize - winning French chemist .

László Fejes Tóth ( Hungarian : Fejes Tóth László , pronounced ( ˈfɛjɛʃ ˈtoːt ˈlaːsloː ) Szeged , 12 March 1915 -- Budapest , 17 March 2005 ) was a Hungarian mathematician who specialized in geometry .
Carlos Luis Federico de Brandsen ( Paris , November 28 , 1785 -- Battle of Ituzaingó , February 20 , 1827 ) was a Coronel of French origin who fought in many of the South American wars of independence and for Argentina in the War with Brazil .

Jean - Louis Victor Grisart ( Paris , 28 June 1797 - Paris , 14 May 1877 ) was a French architect .
Abraham Genoels II or Abraham Genouil ( nickname : Archimedes ) ( 1640 , Antwerp --1723 , Antwerp ) was a Flemish Baroque painter , draughtsman and engraver now mainly known for his landscape drawings and etchings .

Werner Villinger ( 9 October 1887 in Besigheim -- 8 August 1961 near Innsbruck ) was a Nazi German psychiatrist , neurologist , eugenicist and the leading physician at the Bethel Institution ( `` Anstalt Bethel '' ) .
Jan Styka ( April 8 , 1858 in Lwów -- April 11 , 1925 in Rome ) was a Polish painter noted for producing large historical , battle - piece , and Christian religious panoramas .
Selahattin Ülkümen ( 14 January 1914 in Antakya -- 7 June 2003 in Istanbul ) was a Turkish diplomat and consul in Rhodes during the Second World War , who assisted many local Jews to escape the Holocaust .
Ivan Nikitich Konev was born on 5 January 1899 in Sheshminskaya village in Samara Governorate to a peasant family .
Richard Specht ( 7 December 1870 , Vienna - 19 March 1932 ) was an Austrian lyricist , dramatist , musicologist and writer .
Françoise Adnet ( 30 June 1924 - 9 March 2014 ) was a French figurative painter born in Paris .
Felix Maria von Exner - Ewarten ( 23 August 1876 in Vienna -- 7 February 1930 , Vienna ) was an Austrian meteorologist and geophysicist .
Erasmo Bartoli Filippino or Erasmo di Bartolo , called padre Raimo ( 1606 - -1656 ) , was an Italian priest , composer , and teacher at the conservatories in Naples .
Victor Mayer Amédée Mannheim ( 17 July 1831 , Paris , France -- 11 December 1906 , Paris , France ) was the inventor of the modern slide rule .

Joseph Hermann Schmidt ( 1804 - -1852 ) was professor of Obstetrics in Berlin , and official of the Prussian cultural ministry .
Rosario Maceo ( Sr . ) , also known as Papa Rose or Rose Maceo , was a Sicilian immigrant and organized crime boss in Galveston , Texas in the United States .

Johannes Stenrat ( sometimes Hans Stenrat , Stenradh , Stenrat of Lübeck , Stenrode , Steynrot ) c. 1410 - 1484 ) was a German Northern renaissance wood carver and painter , active in Lübeck .
Pietro Gaudenzi ( January 18 , 1880 in Genoa -- December 23 , 1955 in Anticoli Corrado , near Rome ) was an Italian painter .
Conrad Graf ( 17 November 1782 in Riedlingen , Württemberg -- 18 March 1851 in Vienna ) was an Austrian - German piano maker .
César De Paepe ( 12 July 1841 in Ostend , Belgium - 1890 in Cannes , France ) was a medical doctor and a prominent syndicalist whose work strongly influenced the Industrial Workers of the World and the syndicalist movement in general .

Jean - Louis Baudelocque ( November 30 , 1745 -- May 2 , 1810 ) was a French obstetrician who studied and practiced medicine in Paris .
Saint Altfrid ( or Altfrid of Hildesheim ) ( died 15 August 874 ) was a leading figure in Germany in the ninth century .
Soh Hang - suen ( 10 October 1951 -- 12 June 2013 ) , ( alternatively romanised as So Hung - shuen ) , was a Hong Kong actress .

Mikhail Minin was born in 1922 in the village of Vanino , in western Russia 's Pskov Oblast .

Hyacinthe Camille Teisseire ( 22 September 1764 -- 12 September 1842 ) was a French politician and businessman prominent in the civic and industrial life of Grenoble , the city of his birth , during the first half of the 19th century .
Absamat Masaliyevich Masaliyev ( Абсамат Масалиевич Масалиев ) ( April 10 , 1933 , Alysh , Osh oblast , Kyrgyz SSR -- July 31 , 2004 , Bishkek ) was the leader of the Kyrgyz Soviet Socialist Republic before it gained independence , and led the Party of Communists of Kyrgyzstan after the dissolution of the Soviet Union .
Fritz Hoffmann , later Fritz Hoffmann - La Roche ( 1868 , Basel ( French : Bâle ) -- 1920 , Basel ) was the founder of the Hoffmann - La Roche Ltd. ( French : F. Hoffmann - La Roche SA , German : die F. Hoffmann - La Roche AG ) .

Jules Édouard Valtat , who was born August 7 , 1838 in Troyes and died for his country during the Siege of Paris in January 1871 , was a French sculptor .

Agostino Bonisoli ( 1633 - -1700 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , who was born and worked mainly in Cremona .

Adam Śmigielski ( 24 December 1933 in Przemyśl − 7 October 2008 in Sosnowiec ) was a Polish Roman Catholic bishop .
Wahkare Khety was an Ancient Egyptian pharaoh of the 9th or 10th Dynasty during the First Intermediate Period .
Peter Joseph O'Reilly ( April 14 , 1850 -- December 16 , 1923 ) was an Irish - born bishop of the Catholic Church in the United States .
Rob Briley ( born October 15 , 1966 , Nashville , Tennessee , United States ) is an American politician and a Democratic former member of the Tennessee House of Representatives for the 52nd district , which is part of Davidson County .
Ma Ying - jeou ( Chinese : 馬英九 ; pinyin : Mǎ Yīngjiǔ , ( mà jə́ŋtɕjù ) ; born 13 July 1950 ) is a Taiwanese politician who is the current President of the Republic of China ( ROC ) .
David Sigman was an American trade union staff member from Two Rivers , Wisconsin who served three terms as a Republican , then a Progressive member of the Wisconsin State Assembly from the 2nd Manitowoc County district .
Minuccio Minucci ( 1551 - -1604 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic priest who was the archbishop of Zadar .
Petre S. Aurelian ( 13 December 1833 -- 24 January 1909 ) was a Romanian politician who served as a Prime Minister of Romania between 2 December 1896 and 12 April 1897 .
Leon Abbett ( October 8 , 1836 -- December 4 , 1894 ) was an American Democratic Party politician , and lawyer , who served two separate terms as the 26th Governor of New Jersey , from 1884 to 1887 and from 1890 to 1893 .
José Cipriano Castro Ruiz ( 12 October 1858 -- 4 December 1924 ) was a high - ranking member of the Venezuelan military , politician and the President of Venezuela from 1899 to 1908 .
Jean Courtecuisse ( c.1350 , Le Mans - 4 March 1423 , Geneva ) was a French bishop and theologian , who was elected bishop of Paris and bishop of Geneva .
Carlo Odescalchi , ( 5 March 1785 -- 17 August 1841 ) was an Italian prince and priest , archbishop of Ferrara , cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church and Vicar of the Diocese of Rome .
Paul Capdevielle ( January 15 , 1842 -- August 14 , 1922 ) was mayor of New Orleans , Louisiana , from May 9 , 1900 to December 5 , 1904 .
George Distel is a former member of the Ohio House of Representatives , representing the 99th District from 1999 - 2008 .
Laxman Sonopant Joshi ( born 3 April 1935 , death 10 Dec 2014 ) , popularly known as Anna Joshi , is a former member of the Lok Sabha and a leader of Bharatiya Janata Party .
Yves - Alexandre de Marbeuf ( Rennes , 1734-Lübeck , 1799 ) was a French bishop of Autun and archbishop of Lyon , and statesman .
Kimon Georgiev Stoyanov ( Bulgarian : Кимон Георгиев Стоянов ) ( August 11 , 1882 -- September 28 , 1969 ) was a Bulgarian general who was Prime Minister of Bulgaria from 1934 to 1935 and again from 1944 to 1946 .
Harrison Ludington ( July 30 , 1812 -- June 17 , 1891 ) was an American Republican politician who served as the 13th Governor of Wisconsin and a mayor of Milwaukee , Wisconsin .
Chrysippus moved to Athens , where he became the disciple of Cleanthes , who was then the head ( scholarch ) of the Stoic school .
Pietro Pisani ( 1871 - 1960 ) was a Catholic archbishop and diplomat of the Holy See .
D. Devaraj Urs ( 20 August 1915 -- 18 May 1982 ) was an Indian politician who served two terms as the 8th Chief Minister of Karnataka ( 1972 - -77 , 1978 - -80 ) , a state in southern India .
Vernon Sykes ( born October 2 , 1951 ) is a former Democratic member of the Ohio House of Representatives who has represented the 44th District from 2007 to 2014 .
Klaus Wiswe ( born 1955 ) is a German politician , member of the Christian Democratic Union of Germany ( CDU ) and full - time chief executive or Landrat of the North German district of Celle .
Tutankhamun ( /ˌtuːtənkɑːˈmuːn/ ; alternatively spelled with Tutenkh- , -amen , -amon ) was an Egyptian pharaoh of the 18th dynasty ( ruled c. 1332 - -1323 BC in the conventional chronology ) , during the period of Egyptian history known as the New Kingdom .
In 1322 , Andrew of Perugia was nominated bishop of the see of Zaiton by John of Montecorvino .
Nicolas Tiangaye ( born 13 September 1956 ) is a Central African politician and lawyer who was Prime Minister of the Central African Republic from 17 January 2013 until his resignation on 10 January 2014 .
Thomas J. McCormack ( September 28 , 1922 -- August 18 , 1998 ) was a member of the Pennsylvania State Senate , serving during 1978 .
Ioannis Alevras ( Greek : Ιωάννης Αλευράς , 1912 -- 6 April 1995 ) was a Greek Panhellenic Socialist Movement politician and Speaker of the Hellenic Parliament , who served as acting President of Greece in March 1985 .
William Emerson Brock ( March 14 , 1872 -- August 5 , 1950 ) was a Democratic United States Senator from Tennessee from 1929 to 1931 .
Alpheus Felch ( September 28 , 1804 -- June 13 , 1896 ) was the fifth Governor of Michigan and U.S. Senator from Michigan .
Li Kwan Ha , CBE , QPM , CPM ( Chinese : 李君夏 ) was the first ethnic Chinese to serve as the Commissioner of Police in Hong Kong ; he took office in 1989 and retired in 1994 .
Henry Cockshutt ( July 8 , 1868 -- November 26 , 1944 ) was the 13th Lieutenant Governor of Ontario , Canada .
Charles James McDonnell ( born July 1 , 1928 ) is an American retired Roman Catholic titular bishop of Pocofeltus and auxiliary bishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Newark , New Jersey .
Silas Woodson ( May 18 , 1819 -- October 9 , 1896 ) was the 21st Governor of Missouri , United States , between January 3 , 1873 and January 12 , 1875 .

Raphael Nii Amaa Ollennu ( 21 May 1906 -- 22 December 1986 ) was the Chairman of the Presidential Commission and acting President of Ghana during the Second Republic from 7 August 1970 to 31 August 1970 .
Domenico Flabanico ( died 1043 ) was the 29th Doge of Venice .
James Tinker ( April 11 , 1817 -- February 20 , 1886 ) was an American farmer from Rochester , Wisconsin who served a single one - year term as a Free Soil Party member of the Wisconsin State Assembly , in 1851 , from Racine County as well as holding a variety of local offices .
Nicolò da Ponte ( 15 January 1491 - 30 July 1585 ) was the eighty seventh Doge of Venice .

Sylvester Patton is a former member of the Ohio House of Representatives , succeeded by Bob Hagan .
Ceolnoth ( died 870 ) was a medieval English Archbishop of Canterbury .
Peithon was named one of the seven ( later eight ) Somatophylakes `` bodyguards '' of Alexander in 335 BC . After Alexander 's death in 323 BC , Peithon was made the satrap of Media , the strategically important region that controlled all roads between east and west .

Giuseppe Renato Imperiali ( May 1 , 1651 -- February 18 , 1737 ) was an Italian cardinal , and known as an avid bibliophile .

James Madison Wells ( January 8 , 1808 -- February 28 , 1899 ) was elected the 20th Governor of Louisiana during Reconstruction .
Moses Wilson Gray , known as Wilson Gray ( 1813 -- 4 April 1875 ) was an Irish - born barrister , member of the Victorian Legislative Assembly and district judge in New Zealand .
Gnaeus Fulvius Centumalus Maximus ( d. 210 BC ) was a consul of the Roman Republic in 211 BC . As consul , Fulvius defended Rome against Hannibal with his colleague Publius Sulpicius Galba Maximus during the Second Punic War .
William Juxon ( 1582 -- 4 June 1663 ) was an English churchman , Bishop of London from 1633 to 1649 and Archbishop of Canterbury from 1660 until his death .
Nathan Philemon Bryan ( April 23 , 1872 -- August 8 , 1935 ) was a lawyer , federal judge , and United States Senator from Florida .
Joan Ballweg ( born March 16 , 1952 ) is a Wisconsin politician and legislator , currently serving her third term as a member of the Wisconsin State Assembly from the 41st district .

Francesco Minerva ( January 31 , 1904 -- August 23 , 2004 ) was an Italian clergyman ; at his death he was the second - oldest living bishop in the Roman Catholic Church , after Corrado Bafile .

Major Freeman Freeman - Thomas , 1st Marquess of Willingdon GCSI GCMG GCIE GBE PC ( 12 September 1866 -- 12 August 1941 ) was a British Liberal politician and administrator who served as Governor General of Canada , the 13th since Canadian Confederation , and as Viceroy and Governor - General of India , the country 's 22nd .
Johann Philipp Franz von Schönborn ( 1673 - -1724 ) was the Prince - Bishop of Würzburg from 1719 to 1724 .

Luis Mercader Escolano ( 1444 - -1516 ) was the Grand Inquisitor of the Kingdom of Aragon from 1513 to 1516 .

The Naked Runner is a 1967 British espionage film directed by Sidney J. Furie and starring Frank Sinatra , Peter Vaughan and Edward Fox .

Kimberly Barber ( born December 21 , 1959 ) is a Canadian mezzo - soprano and vocal pedagogue .
Gregory Stapp is an American bass who has performed actively in concerts and operas internationally for more than 35 years .
Montserrat Caballé ( Catalan : ( munsəˈrat kəβəˈʎe ) ; born 12 April 1933 ) is a Spanish operatic soprano .
Monica Yunus ( born 1979 ) is an American operatic soprano who has performed with many opera companies and music ensembles .
Rita Hunter CBE ( 15 August 1933 -- 29 April 2001 ) was a British operatic dramatic soprano .
Henri Legay ( Paris , July 1 , 1920 -- Paris , September 16 , 1992 ) was a French operatic tenor .
Christina Maria Avoglio or Avolia ( floruit , 1740 - -1744 ) was an Italian soprano in Handel 's opera company .
Nicholas Clapton ( born 16 September 1955 ) is an English countertenor , singing - teacher and author .
Kathryn Grayson ( February 9 , 1922 -- February 17 , 2010 ) was an American actress and soprano .
Gertrude Grob - Prandl ( 11 November 1917 -- 16 May 1995 ) was an Austrian Wagnerian soprano .
Levi Stubbs ( June 6 , 1936 -- October 17 , 2008 ) was an American baritone singer , best known as the lead vocalist of the R&B group the Four Tops , a band known for a variety of Motown hit records and other songs created in the 1960s and 1970s .
Janai Brugger ( born 1983 ) is an American operatic soprano who has won several major music competitions and has appeared in leading roles with several American opera companies .
Simona Houda - Šaturová is a Slovak classical soprano who has had an active international career performing in operas , concerts , and recitals since the early 1990s .
Gino Bechi ( 16 October 1913 -- 2 February 1993 ) was an Italian operatic baritone , particularly associated with the Italian repertory , especially in Verdi roles .
Leo Slezak ( German pronunciation : ( ˌleːo ˈslɛzak ) ; 18 August 1873 -- 1 June 1946 ) was a world - famous Moravian tenor .
Raymond Jean - Baptiste Ernest Carbonne ( 30 July 1860 in Toulouse -- 1924 ) was a French tenor and stage director who had a long association with the Opéra - Comique in Paris .
Franz Ferenczy ( also Franz Friedemann ) ( 1835 -- 27 February 1881 , Weimar ) was a nineteenth - century German tenor who had a prolific opera career in Europe between 1859 - 1880 .
http://onstageartists.com/trond-halstein-moe-uk/Trond Halstein Moe ( born December 20 , 1954 , Trondheim , Norway ) is a Norwegian operatic baritone .
Gustavus Waltz ( fl . 1732 - 1759 ) was a German bass opera singer who collaborated with Handel .
Maria Theresia Löw ( 27 March 1809 -- 30 December 1885 ) was a German operatic soprano and harpist .
Sylvia Sass ( born 12 July 1951 ) is a Hungarian operatic soprano who has sung leading roles both in her native country and internationally .
Maria Chiara ( born 24 November 1939 ) is an Italian lyric soprano .
Stefania Woytowicz ( 8 October 1922 , Orynyn , Kamianets - Podilskyi Raion -- 31 August 2005 , Warsaw ) was a Polish concert soprano .
Giuseppe de Begnis ( 1793 - 10 August 1849 ) was an operatic bass singer .

Nick Afoa ( born 1986 in Auckland ) is a New Zealand tenor and former New Zealand age grade rugby player of Samoan and Croatian heritage .
Graciela Araya ( born May 16 , 1962 ) is an Austrian mezzo - soprano of Chilean birth who has had a prolific international opera career since the early 1980s .
Maria Dragoni ( born 22 December 1958 ) is an Italian operatic soprano active international career in major opera house from 1984 to present .
Mary Garden ( 20 February 1874 -- 3 January 1967 ) , was a Scottish operatic soprano with a substantial career in France and America in the first third of the 20th century .
Yolanda Soares is a Portuguese soprano singer , songwriter and `` crossover '' solo artist .
Nicola Zerola ( 1876 -- 21 July 1936 ) was an Italian operatic tenor who had an active international career from 1898 - 1928 .
Bertha Schwarz , often known by her stage name Bianca Bianchi , was a coloratura soprano opera singer of the late 19th century .
Suzanne Juyol ( January 1 , 1920 , Paris -- July 20 , 1994 , Paris ) was a French opera singer , the leading dramatic soprano of her era in France .
Julian Patrick ( 26 October 1927 - 8 May 2009 ) was an American operatic baritone and voice teacher .
Mercedes Capsir ( Catalan pronunciation : ( mərˈsɛðəs kəpˈsi ) ) ( 20 July 1895 - 13 March 1969 ) was a Catalan Spanish opera singer , a high coloratura soprano , particularly associated with light Italian roles , such as Lucia and Gilda .
Giacomo David ( born Giacomo Davide , Presezzo , 1750 -- Bergamo , 1830 ) , was a leading Italian tenor of the late 18th and early 19th centuries .
Marie Powers ( 1902 - -1973 ) was an American contralto who was best known for her performance as Madame Flora in Gian Carlo Menotti 's The Medium , a role that she played on stage , screen and television .
Axel Köhler ( born 1959 in Schwarzenberg , Saxony ) is a German countertenor and opera director .
Józef Michał Poniatowski ( Rome , July 24 , 1814 -- London , July 4 , 1873 ) was a Polish szlachcic , a composer and an operatic tenor .
Marianne Mathy - Frisdane ( 23 June 1890 -- 18 October 1978 ) was a coloratura soprano opera singer and distinguished teacher of opera and classical singing .
Margaret Keys is an Irish soprano with Universal Records .
Anna Krauja Čena ( born 1981 ) is a lyric soprano from Latvia .
Mac Morgan ( June 25 , 1917 -- June 12 , 2007 ) was an American bass - baritone who had an active performance career in concerts and operas from the early 1940s until the mid-1970s .
Arturo Chacón Cruz ( August 20 , 1977 ) is a Mexican operatic tenor .
Marie - Gabrielle Krauss ( 24 March 1842 -- 6 January 1906 ) was an important 19th century Austrian - born French operatic soprano .
Gail Dubinbaum ( born 1957 ) is an American operatic coloratura mezzo - soprano and co - founder and Creative Director of the Phoenix Metropolitan Opera .
Theo Adam ( born 1 August 1926 ) is a distinguished German classical bass - baritone who had an active international career in operas , concerts , and recitals from the 1940s through the 1990s .
Margreta Elkins AM ( 16 October 1930 -- 1 April 2009 ) was an Australian mezzo - soprano of great renown .
Pierre de La Garde ( 10 February 1717 , Crécy - la - Chapelle -- 1792 ) was a French composer and baritone .
Paulina Rivoli ( 22 July 1823 - 12 October 1881 ) was a Polish operatic soprano who had an active international career with important European opera houses from 1837 - 1860 .
Vyatcheslav Kagan - Paley , also known as Slava ( `` Слава '' Каган-Палей ) , is a Belarusian countertenor and male alto .
Virginia Guerrini ( 20 February 1871 , Brescia -- 26 February 1948 , Brescia ) was an Italian operatic mezzo - soprano .
Mary Davies ( 27 February 1855 -- 22 June 1930 ) was a Welsh mezzo - soprano and the co - founder and first President of the Welsh Folk Song Society .
